neighborhood_overview: Montjuïc is most likely the best neighborhood in Girona. We are up in a hill, only 15-20 minutes to the center of the city, and surrounded by Nature. it is very safe and quiet.
host_about:
It's hard to define oneself in such a narrow space. I think we people are really complex material. But since I guess it's good I say a bit, I would define myself as someone fascinated about living and getting to know both this planet and its inhabitants. I'm interested in serving people, especially, but not exclusively, my friends. I enjoy good food and if possible better company. My interests are broad and go from traveling, literature, creative writing, philosophy and body "care" to Buddhism.  I'm pushful, curious, a bit narcissist maybe, hahaha, and I guess I tend to dream pies in the sky far too often.

I am original Catalan, from lovely Girona - Costa Brava but I've lived abroad for many long periods: Miami, Dubai, Bali and Melbourne (Australia). My live partner is a lovely aussie-greek Personal Trainer named Stelios and, together we travel the world, when not working.

I like outdoors sports and I am addicted to mountain biking. I also like snowboarding, climbing, hiking, swimming ...; I also do some mat work like yoga and Pilates (of which I am a certified Instructor). 

I read a lot, books facinate me!!

I like to go out eating with my friends from time to time, although I am most of a day-creature and at night I like my sleep. I practice ioga and meditation and have a second level on Reiki. I'm a flexitarian (meaning I eat fish but not meat) by moral reasons and I enjoy a lot good food, if possible made with organic products. Music, all kind of music - depending on the moment - is very important to me; couldn't live without it. But my main and huge passion is travelling and meeting new people, travellers like me, or locals, and learn about them and their experiences in life. 

After many yearts working for others, I am now running my my own company. It's a fresh project dedicated to giving marketing and creativity services & solutions to other companies. I am also a teacher at the University of Girona, where I teach at the Faculties of Tourism and Economics and I run an international women's project named "Grace of No Age", devoted to mature women.

I am pretty busy however I don't complain, as I do what I like.

Welcome!

description:
NUESTRA ACOGEDORA CASA ESTA DENTRO DEL PARQUE NATURAL DE LA ZONA VOLCANICA DE LA GARROTXA Y A CINCO MINUTOS DE OLOT. TIENE TRES HABITACIONES CON BAÑO EN SU INTERIOR, COCINA, UN AMPLIO SALON CON CHIMENEA Y BARBACOA EN EL JARDIN

The space
Caserío del siglo XIV reformado y totalmente equipado, situado en pleno Parque Natural de la zona Volcánica de la Garrotxa. Es uno de los lugares más bonitos del Parque, combina bosques, pastos y algunos caseríos aislados con chozas y muros de piedra seca de roca volcánica. En este paraje de múltiples leyendas es donde se originaron los primeros volcanes, ahora solo testimoniados por diferentes coladas de lava, ya enfriadas y superpuestas una encima de la otra, que configuran un relieve suave.
A cinco minutos del famoso Hayedo d’en Jordà, Volcán Santa Margarita, Volcán Croscat y la Ciudad de Olot.
Cuenta con un comedor sala de estar con chimenea, un gran distribuidor, una cocina totalmente equipada, tres habitaciones,

name: Quiet times by the riverside
description:
Stay in a historical building! Right in the Old Town, you will have shops, restaurants and walks literally round the corner. Very quiet, with wide views on the river. Parking is about 5 minutes walk. Long stays welcome. No late arrival fees.

The space
Days for a great break in the historical centre of a small pretty city!
The apartment is in the heart of the old town, on a privileged location: right in front of the riverside. So you'll see the birds fishing in the morning, and the sun sets will just be yours, on a huge 4 meters wide window on the river.
In addition to the views, the silence is one of the pros of the apartment; the river is very quiet, and as I live on the apartment below your you won't have parties every night (or you'll be one in it! :) )
The place has one big room; on one side the bed, very comfortable and wide, and on the other the sofa-bed and the computer. It doesn't feel small as the ceiling is very high, and a nice (sort of
neighborhood_overview: I believe we live in one of the best places in the world. It has the advantages of a city, but actually is is still a town- in the good way! Iis a lively area with many places to visit, shops, or simply walk around. I specially love the gardens around the city wall, 10 minutes from here. I deeply appreciate that cars are restricted in the area.
host_about:
I am someone who likes very different things, you will see. Let's start: I was born in a small town in l'Empordà, called Torroella de Montgrí. Those were also a mixture of happy and wild times, a bit like Amarcord from Fellini (watch it if you haven't).
Then I studied computer science in Barcelona, and a PhD with a part of it in London, about medical imaging.
In between something entered my life, for good: yoga: I started practicing and soon I was so pationated then when I finished my PhD it was obvious that becoming a teaching would be the best choice of my life.
So I practice yoga every day, and also: I love music, and I play myself the accordeon and the clarinet. Just as an amateur, but the pleasure of making music is amazing. I also like dancing, folk music and lately also Lindy Hop (Girona has a few places to dance if you are into it).
I like eating well and healthy. Not to much meat (I am sorry for those creatures we kill but sometimes it comes and I eat).
I like travelling, in all wild ways, but I am not a traveller that can tell thousands things! I participate as well in the couchsurfing project, from time to time- and when there isn't already someone at my place, a friend or a friend of a friend.
The apartment I rent, Girona Riverside, was planned to be for me as another floor was ment to be the yoga studio. However now I have another, bigger, place for yoga and I rent it. I hope you like it!
As a buddhist (if I can call myself that which I don't know) my motto would be to understand the sources of suffering, and enjoy immediate happyness.
Hola!Soy David!Soy profesor de yoga y os invito a una estancia estupenda en el centro de Girona en un apartamento con unas increibles vistas al rio!Naturaleza y silencio para tu felicidad!

host_about:
Tengo 50 años y administro mis propiedades como actividad principal. 
Mi último proyecto ha sido hacerme con la propiedad de una Masia en la frontera del Gironés con la Garrotxa, a 30 minutos de la entrada de Girona. 
Me ocupo del mantenimiento de la Masía, su jardín y bosque, me procuran trabajo de ajardinar, limpieza del bosque, cuidado del pequeño huerto (por ahora) además de ocuparme de las obras de restauración de la Masía. 
Aprecio de mis clientes que sepan valorar el comfort y la calidad de los espacios que me he dedicado a restaurar. Me tomo muy en serio el aspecto de dejar las viviendas en perfectas condiciones, con todos sus detalles, además de darles un estilo clássico y natural gacias a la ayuda de mi mujer Bea que tiene un buen gusto para los detalles.
Me gusta el orden y la limpieza, y espero de la gente que así lo sean. 
Somos una pareja que apreciamos tener gente de todas las edades. Apreciamos la gente que busca un sitio auténtico donde pasar unos días tanto buscando la tranquilidad como para festejar con amigos.

name: Together w family·friends in cozy apartment-lofts!
description:
Organize a holiday reunion together with family members or friends. We have 3 apartments for an independent stay use with central-heating for 3 fam. or 13 'pers. You can apart hire an extra separate large room having a wood stove celebrating a party.

The space
Can Banal is a former Catalan farmhouse called "masía" from the XVI century. Since 1987 it has been our home and camping business. Since 2012 we have been able to open up 3 holiday apartments on the upper floor that can be rented all 3 together for a group, specially 3 or 4 families "together but not mixed". The apartments can accommodate 3 '- 5' - 6 '= 14 persons in total. Besides there is a large room, beware rather rustic style, for a party event. We rent it out apart including a simple kitchen, wood stove with firewood and music-equipment. Consult us the price.

The apartments are independent multi space rooms containing bedroom, kitchen with dining area and bathroom. All have central heating
neighborhood_overview:
Can Banal is situated in the beginning of the Catalan Pyrenees, in a region called “Alta Garrotxa”. Located midway between the sea-shore (45 min) and the high mountains of the Pyrenees (1h) makes it possible for many types of day-trips.
Close to many interesting places of cultural, natural or gourmet aspects like Castelfullit de la Roca, Besalu, the Garrotxa Volcanic Park or Olot.
Within a 6 km drive, Sadernes is reached from where the wonderful trekking path towards Sant Aniol d'Aguja starts.

The landscape around Can Banal is peaceful and rural, with rivers and forests that changes colors depending on the season. In autumn there are varieties of mushrooms and in spring many types of orchids and butterflies to enjoy.

If you just decides to stay around in Can Banal you'll find enough to do for few days. Walk our own signed trails along water creeks, fields, forests, hermitage, farms and villages round us. We have mountain bike’s to rent and in a 25' walk
host_about:
Hola, we are Stendert & Maria

We live in Mas Can Banal for many years. Stendert, born '51, originally is from Breda-Holland, and Maria, born '66, is from Stockholm-Sweden, where her parents once had arrived from Spain. We enjoy very much living here in the countryside surrounded by hills, forests, and rivers. Halfway to the sea and to the high mountains.

We are accompanied by our daughter Saskia born '02 and Stendert's son - Luuk, born  '93, who works in our village and in their spare time help us.

Our professions are of the most diverse; Maria studied interior design and artistic glass techniques and Stendert studied to become a tropical agronomist and later carpentry. Probably this multifaceted mixture connects us with many diverse interests and activities, especially the maintenance of CB with its forest, animals, and agro-tourism.

We hope to be able to combine these aspects of us and make your stay as pleasant and memorable as possible. Together, we speak 7 European languages and understand a few more. We like very much to tell you about our favorite places, help you out for more personal advice and add if there is a special event going on.

  Welcome·Bienvenidos·Welkom·Benvinguts·Välmommen·Bienvenue·Willkommen

Hola somos Maria and Stendert

Vivimos en Mas Can Banal desde hace muchos años. Stendert, nacido '51, originario de Breda , Holanda y María, nacida '66, de Estocolmo- Suecia , donde sus padres una vez llegaron desde España . Nos gusta mucho vivir aquí en el campo, rodeado de colinas, bosques y ríos. A mitad de camino hacia el mar y la mitad del camino a las altas montañas.

Nos acompaña nuestra hija Saskia, nacida '02 y Luuk, hijo de Stendert,  nacido en el '93, que trabaja en nuestro pueblo. Ambos en sus ratos libres nos ayudan en diferentes tareas.

Nuestras profesiones son de la más diversa; María estudió diseño de interiores y técnicas de vidrio artístico y Stendert estudió para ser ingeniero agrónomo tropical y mas tarde carpintería. Probablemente esta mezcla multifacética , nos conecta con muchos diversos intereses y actividades, en especial el mantenimiento de CB con su bosque, los animales y el agroturismo.

Esperamos ser capaces de combinar estos aspectos de nosotros y como hacer que su estancia sea lo más agradable y memorable como sea posible. En conjunto, se habla 7 idiomas europeos y entender algunos pocos más. Nos gusta mucho que decir acerca de nuestros lugares favoritos, ayudará a cabo el asesoramiento más personal y añadir si hay un evento especial ocurre.

description:
Located in a small family residence, with only a small sent between the residence and the sea, the apartment with 2 bedrooms can pleasantly host a family of 4.

View from terrace is spectacular, since there is no obstacle between the apartment and sea. From the terrace , Medes Islands as well as all of the Roses bay are visible.

To go and swim, one only needs to get down into the small cove in front of the apartment.

7' away walking, there is a supermarket and a restaurant.

The space
The residence is made of 2 small buildings plus the residence keeper place, 3 parking areas, a 2-part swimming pool for residence members only, a garden and a direct access to sea .

Located on the top right end corner of the second building, the apartment has 2 bedrooms, and is fully equipped.

One well located parking space comes with the apartment.

The apartment has a front row view of the Roses Bay.

The
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in a family residence made of 2 small buildings.

The view from the terrace is exceptional because there is only a coastal trail between the apartment residence and the sea.

The apartment is on the fourth and last floor on the corner of the second building.

From the terrace, one can see all of Roses Bay (220 square km), and the Medes Islands located 21 km away, on the other side of the Bay.

And to go swimming, all you need to do is to walk down into the cove located in front of the residence.
host_about:
French and Canadian, married to a Spanish Catalan, with 3 daughters, including 1 American, I like to travel and meet people from all countries and different walks of life.

As a host, I am flexible and understanding as long as the guest respects my property and her/his engagements.

As a guest, I appreciate a caring host and I respect her/his property and leave up to my terms of the deal.

If any life motto, mine is: "keep on growing, with an open heart".

I do quite a lot of horse back riding, skiing and scuba diving.
I have a motor bike that I ride almost daily.

On the leisure side, I like to read in English, Spanish and French. 

I have eclectic tastes in music, movie and art, ranging from Mozart to Adele, Ingmar Bergman to Steven Soderberg, Michelangelo to Bastia.

I believe it is never too late to start new things in life and I am very close to my wife and family.

Amplio dormitorio c
neighborhood_overview: Situada en una urbanización tranquila, en la falda de una colina con vistas al mar y  rodeada de naturaleza,  donde viven vecinos del pueblo todo el año, a 5 minutos en coche de supermercados,  centro y playas.
host_about:
Hola, somos Manolo e Isabel, 
Desde Villalloret queremos  darles  la bienvenida. Este alojamiento que en principio nació para uso personal, para albergar reuniones familiares y vivir momentos únicos con familia y amigos, fue decorado con todo amor, por eso está lleno de pequeños toques con  sabor rural, para  los que utilizamos útiles de labranza propiedad de la familia.
Tiempo después vimos que por la dinámica de la vida diaria  no podíamos hacer uso de él y disfrutarlo nada más que en determinadas ocasiones,  y así fue como decidimos ponerlo a disposición para que otras familias pudieran disfrutarlo y pasar aquí  su tiempo de vacaciones, e incluso teletrabajar si este fuera su caso. 
Por eso nos  encantaría que pudieran conocer la Costa Brava desde  una perspectiva diferente, combinando el sabor de antaño, con lo actual, combinando el mar y la montaña, en un espacio para evadirse y reencontrarse con la naturaleza y con un ritmo más lento en su vida diaria más auténtico y sostenible. Pero a  la vez y cercano a lo urbano, a lugares de ocio y a las mejores playas de la costa Brava

Es una autentica casa de pueblo ubicada en el casco antiguo de Pals, uno de los pueblos medievales con mayor encanto del Ampurdan. Tiene un premio de Bellas Artes.
Excelente comunicación con Barcelona, Gerona y Francia.
La casa esta ubicada en el llamado triangulo de oro, muy cerca de la playa de Pals a 4Km. así como de otras playas de aguas de color turquesa muy bonitas.
Hay innumerables y auténticos pueblos medievales para visitar, así como el Museo Dali ubicado en el pueblo de Figueras y el castillo de Pubol donde se encuentra enterrada Gala la mujer de Dali.
Pals esta a una distancia de 35 Km. de Gerona, una ciudad interesante para conocer ... barrio judío, catedral, etc...

Alegre y con muchas ganas de vivir y de disfrutar con mis amigos organizando eventos diferentes: comidas con vinito, ver películas, exposiciones de Arte, salidas en bicicleta...

name: Els Racons del Fort: Castle in wine territory
description:
A stone building from 1694 having a shape of a fortified castle in the village of Capmany only 14 minutes away from Figueres and 26 minutes from Roses.

The fortified construction has a big garden, two terraces, and a covered outdoor space with a pergola. Swimming pool will be ready April 2022.

Capmany has more than ten wineries and your host Yves can teach you about local cuisine in form of: private dinners, hands-on cooking classes, or local experiences visiting wineries and food producers.

The space
The house offers a very unique feeling of the history that has happened inside and outside its walls. It has been renovated in a very respectful way and host Eli has decorated the house to make you feel good during your stay.

For family gatherings, it is possible to rent the apartments too and come together in the garden and pool.

There is also a huge diaphanous space very suitable for diverse activities such as retreats
neighborhood_overview: Capmany is a village with 614 inhabitants and more than 10 wine cellers. Beautiful walks can be done and the closest beach is a 26 min drive away.
host_about:
I was born in Switzerland and live in Barcelona since I am 8 years old.  I love cooking and I have decided to move from online marketing (10 years working in the field) to Cooking Workshops and private cooking events, following my passion in life.

host_about:
Soy una mujer mediterránea que no podría vivir sin la luz del sol, la buena comida ni muy lejos del mar . Me gusta escribir, leer, la música y el buen cine. Y nadar en las playas de Palamós,  donde he pasado los veranos desde  mi infancia.

description:
This is a 200 year-old historic house rehabilitated by a local architect in the center of medieval town Besalu (Girona), with peaceful garden where to disconnect from the world. County of Garrotxa, a remarkable region plenty of outdoor options.

The space
House is suitable for two families (max capacity is eight), with a private garden and a small natural pool (no chemical depurator). Walking distance from main facilities (supermarket, bakery, press, etc.). Situated in the inner center of old town. Restricted access to cars.

Guest access
Three-level house with private garden. Small natural pool (in the garden). House is fully equipped for self-catering and has washing machine too.

Other things to note
Visit the official Website of Besalu and of the Garrotxa region to learn more about what to do; it's amazing!

Satuna is the smallest, most romantic and quiet of the three coves of the municipality of Begur (Costa Brava - Girona). Has managed to preserve the air and the size that his former fishermen gave him. And its tranquility is only disturbed by the winds of East and Tramontana.

description:
Charming appartment in an ancient mill-farmhouse in a green peaceful valley, between the Costa Brava and the Pyrinees. Perfect place for a relaxed holiday in the country.
July minimun nights 4
August minimun nights 7.
Swimming-pool shared from june to september.
Children under 14 have to go aconpagnated in the pool by an adult (over 18 yerars old).

The space
Our house, El Moli d'en Solà, is a Catalan farmhouse situated in a privileged environment for its beauty and peacefulness. It dates back to the fourteenth century. The house is surrounded by meadows and forests and the river that moved the mill is clean and perfect for swimming. If you find it too cold you can also bath in the pool(open from june to september)

Guest access
The house has a large communal green area with playground playground and football goal.
Each unit has access to its own BBQ and shared pool (open from June to September ).
The old mill
neighborhood_overview:
The house is at the bottom of a valley in a rural area with few isolated farmhouses. It is a green and quiet corner, away from the madding crowd but only 5 minutes from the village.
We are in the region of La Garrotxa, which is famous for its volcanoes, the Fageda d'En Jorda and medieval villages like Santa Pau, Besalu. It is an excellent starting point for trips to the Costa Brava or the Pyrenees, as we are between the two sites.
host_about: We are a family in love with the place where we live. It's a special place and we want to share it with people. That's why part of our house has appartments for guests.

neighborhood_overview:
Can Banal is situated in the beginning of the Catalan Pyrenees, in a region called “Alta Garrotxa”. Located midway between the sea-shore (45 min) and the high mountains of the Pyrenees (1h) makes it possible for many types of day-trips.
Close to many interesting places of cultural, natural or gourmet aspects like Castelfullit de la Roca, Besalu, the Garrotxa Volcanic Park or Olot.
Within a 6 km drive, Sadernes is reached from where the wonderful trekking path towards Sant Aniol d'Aguja starts.

The landscape around Can Banal is peaceful and rural, with rivers and forests that changes colours depending on the season. In autumn there are varieties of mushrooms and in spring many types of orquids and butterflies to enjoy.

host_about:
Hola, we are Stendert & Maria

We live in Mas Can Banal for many years. Stendert, born '51, originally is from Breda-Holland, and Maria, born '66, is from Stockholm-Sweden, where her parents once had arrived from Spain. We enjoy very much living here in the countryside surrounded by hills, forests, and rivers. Halfway to the sea and to the high mountains.

We are accompanied by our daughter Saskia born '02 and Stendert's son - Luuk, born  '93, who works in our village and in their spare time help us.

Our professions are of the most diverse; Maria studied interior design and artistic glass techniques and Stendert studied to become a tropical agronomist and later carpentry. Probably this multifaceted mixture connects us with many diverse interests and activities, especially the maintenance of CB with its forest, animals, and agro-tourism.

We hope to be able to combine these aspects of us and make your stay as pleasant and memorable as possible. Together, we speak 7 European languages and understand a few more. We like very much to tell you about our favorite places, help you out for more personal advice and add if there is a special event going on.

  Welcome·Bienvenidos·Welkom·Benvinguts·Välmommen·Bienvenue·Willkommen

Hola somos Maria and Stendert

Vivimos en Mas Can Banal desde hace muchos años. Stendert, nacido '51, originario de Breda , Holanda y María, nacida '66, de Estocolmo- Suecia , donde sus padres una vez llegaron desde España . Nos gusta mucho vivir aquí en el campo, rodeado de colinas, bosques y ríos. A mitad de camino hacia el mar y la mitad del camino a las altas montañas.

Nos acompaña nuestra hija Saskia, nacida '02 y Luuk, hijo de Stendert,  nacido en el '93, que trabaja en nuestro pueblo. Ambos en sus ratos libres nos ayudan en diferentes tareas.

Nuestras profesiones son de la más diversa; María estudió diseño de interiores y técnicas de vidrio artístico y Stendert estudió para ser ingeniero agrónomo tropical y mas tarde carpintería. Probablemente esta mezcla multifacética , nos conecta con muchos diversos intereses y actividades, en especial el mantenimiento de CB con su bosque, los animales y el agroturismo.

Esperamos ser capaces de combinar estos aspectos de nosotros y como hacer que su estancia sea lo más agradable y memorable como sea posible. En conjunto, se habla 7 idiomas europeos y entender algunos pocos más. Nos gusta mucho que decir acerca de nuestros lugares favoritos, ayudará a cabo el asesoramiento más personal y añadir si hay un evento especial ocurre.

name: Space Oasis - a tranquil and stylish retreat.
description:
Space Oasis is your haven of peace and quiet just a stones throw away from the beautiful beaches and bustling towns of the fabulous Costa Brava - a truly welcoming escape for friends & family to settle back, relax and unwind - hammock in the garden, a dip in the pool, fire pit BBQ, dinner & drinks on the terrace and total privacy as the space is all yours. Bliss!

The space
Space Oasis Holiday Villa is the perfect destination for groups of up to 12 people looking for somewhere a little bit special. We had a lot of fun creating the 'Pop Art' guest accommodation and love sharing our distinctive home with appreciative and laid-back friends from all over the globe.

Our living spaces are split into sections all accessible from a large central courtyard with 100 m2 terrace & 10 x 5 m swimming pool. The main guest house has 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms and a lovely spacious open plan kitchen/diner/living area with a wall of glass doors opening out to the terrace
neighborhood_overview: The setting is really special and unique. We enjoy lots of peace, quiet and tons of privacy but are just minutes away from some of the most stunning old towns and fabulous beaches in Europe. Pals old town is truly unique with narrow stone streets and a multitude of great restaurants and shops and Begur, Girona and Barcelona are of course bucket list places to visit.  If action and activities tickle your fancy then there is fab scuba diving on the Illes Medes a few minutes drive away plus skiing in the Pyrenees, road and mountain biking, great walking routes and beaches & sparkling little coves to die for all up and down the coast.
host_about:
Welcome to our Space Oasis! My name is Amalia, I am English/Canadian and my husband Dani is Russian. We met here on the Costa Brava, have lived here for almost 15 years. We speak EspanglishRuss together!

I work from home whereas Dani manages a super yacht in Barcelona and is often out 'at sea'. We both enjoy travelling and finding adventure when we can doing outdoorsy stuff like motorbiking or cycling; on-and-off road, horse riding and long dog hikes, but more often than not we're both working or relaxing in the garden at home. Well, to be honest, usually Dani is doing the gardening whilst I practise juggling, hula hoop, poi - or whatever is the latest skill I'm learning off YouTube!
 I'm a passionate animal lover and have 2 dogs, 8 cats and 1 horse. When I'm relaxing I love to just hang out with my animals and read a book. Guests have full access to my large library of books. Quite a few are beach-read best sellers - perfect for holidaymakers.

As we are often out-and-about our good friend Amber Jane will help you with  enquiries and bookings in the first instance and I will meet you when you arrive at Space Oasis Holiday Villa.

I will be here to help you get settled in but once I give you the keys my house is yours to enjoy in your own way. 

I like to share my house with good people , all I ask is that you respect my belongings and we both respect each others privacy. Other than that: 
Eat, Drink, Swim and Make Merry!

Vivimos en Mas Can Banal desde hace muchos años. Stendert, nacido '51, originario de Breda , Holanda y María, nacida '66, de Estocolmo- Suecia , donde sus padres una vez llegaron desde España . Nos gusta mucho vivir aquí en el campo, rodeado de colinas, bosques y ríos. A mitad de camino hacia el mar y la mitad del camino a las altas montañas.

Nos acompaña nuestra hija Saskia, nacida '02 y Luuk, hijo de Stendert,  nacido en el '93, que trabaja en nuestro pueblo. Ambos en sus ratos libres nos ayudan en diferentes tareas.

Nuestras profesiones son de la más diversa; María estudió diseño de interiores y técnicas de vidrio artístico y Stendert estudió para ser ingeniero agrónomo tropical y mas tarde carpintería. Probablemente esta mezcla multifacética , nos conecta con muchos diversos intereses y actividades, en especial el mantenimiento de CB con su bosque, los animales y el agroturismo.

Esperamos ser capaces de combinar estos aspectos de nosotros y como hacer que su estancia sea lo más agradable y memorable como sea posible. En conjunto, se habla 7 idiomas europeos y entender algunos pocos más. Nos gusta mucho que decir acerca de nuestros lugares favoritos, ayudará a cabo el asesoramiento más personal y añadir si hay un evento especial ocurre.

name: Luxury Villa&Spa, 10m from the sea
description:
MAS TORROELLA is a superbly restored Catalan farmhouse dating from the 14th Century. A large and roomy property both inside and out, the house radiates unassuming grandeur and luxury yet has all the home comforts, mod-cons and facilities such as its own spa, sauna, gym, tennis court and outdoor swimming pool.

The space
Thanks to its excellent location, guests can disconnect and enjoy complete privacy and seclusion at Mas Torroella which is set amid protected pine and cork forests. Yet just a short drive away, you find rustic villages dotted along the coast and inland where you can discover the essence, the character and gastronomy of this romantic region.

Mas Torroella´s scrupulous restoration highlights some amazing details such as Baroque style hand-painted ceiling friezes, traditional stone windows and rustic stone walls. These features combine with grace and luxurious finishing touches to give a lasting unique, magical feeling the moment you step f
neighborhood_overview: sin registro
host_about:
Mas Torroella was built in the XIV century. When my father bought it in 1989 it was an abandoned stone ruin crying to be loved and cared for by somebody... And he spent most of his life rebuilding it, investing all his love and passion to create his dream. When my father passed away, my husband and I decided to fulfill his dream and complete the restoration... now our historic masia has been turned into a charming luxury villa & spa.
Most of our guests agree that you can feel peace, tranquility and love inside and outside our house. We are proud of it and must admit that, after a long and hard period of restoration, it has been worthwhile.
We have really put lots of effort and lots of love in restoring it... and I hope this can be seen in the result...

I am sure the Villa will be up to your standards and that you will be able to enjoy the holiday you have wished for, here with us in the Costa Brava.
We will do our best to make it happen!

Cerdanya is a mountainous region with a high flat only because it is one of the wider valleys of Europe, between the Moixeró and the Pyrenees. In Cerdanya can find scenic beauty and diversity that make it unique.

Time in this region is variable, but mostly sunny throughout the year. The slopes have a high high mountain climate, while the lower slopes and plains enjoy a continental Mediterranean climate prone mountainous, with cold winters and cool summers.

In Cerdanya can enjoy variety of outputs, meadows, forests, beech, mountain ranges, massive rivers, lakes, peaks, a unique ... that offers a wide range of possibilities.

neighborhood_overview:
Palafrugell – Costa Brava
A pocos quilómetros del mar y la montaña, Palafrugell es un municipio de la comarca del Baix Empordà, en plena Costa Brava, en el que puedes encontrar la tranquilidad del mundo rural o el movimiento de un importante destino turístico.
Rodeado de naturaleza puedes descubrir las calas más representativas de la Costa Brava como Calella, Llafranc, Tamariu y Agua Xelida y a la vez practicar excursiones por el macizo Les Gavarres, el GR-92 por los caminos de ronda de la Costa Brava o por las vías verdes del municipio.
Palafrugell es perfecto para disfrutar en pareja, familia y amigos.
host_about: Soy madre de dos niños y profesora de yoga. Vivo en la casa restaurada de mis abuelos, y después de unos años viviendo en ciudades grandes he vuelto a mis orígenes para así poder darles a mis hijos la calidad de vida que se merecen. Disfruto mucho de la naturaleza que hay en este entorno maravilloso que es l'Empordà.

name: El Molí d' en Solà. Golfes Oest PG 204
description:
Charming appartment in an ancient mill-farmhouse in a green peaceful valley, between the Costa Brava and the Pyrinees. Perfect place for a relaxed holiday in the country.

The space
Our house, El Moli d'en Solà, is a Catalan farmhouse situated in a privileged environment for its beauty and peacefulness. It dates back to the fourteenth century. The house is surrounded by meadows and forests and the river that moved the mill is clean and perfect for swimming. If you find it too cold you can also bathe in the pool.

Guest access
The house has a large communal green area with playground
Each unit has access to its own BBQ and shared pool (open from June 1 to September 31).
The old mill and a small collection of antique farm tools can be visited.
We also have a small farm where children can meet our chickens, ponies, pigs, donkeys ...

PG-000204
neighborhood_overview:
The house is at the bottom of a valley in a rural area with few isolated farmhouses. It is a green and quiet corner, away from the madding crowd but only 5 minutes from the village.
We are in the region of La Garrotxa, which is famous for its volcanoes, the Fageda d'En Jorda and medieval villages like Santa Pau, Besalu. It is an excellent starting point for trips to the Costa Brava or the Pyrenees, as we are between the two sites.
host_about: We are a family in love with the place where we live. It's a special place and we want to share it with people. That's why part of our house has appartments for guests.

Apartamento 14 avo piso, situado en el centro de Palamós, con vistas espectaculares a primera línea de playa. Tiene 1 habitación doble, 1 baño con bañera, cocina, un salón-comedor con sofá-cama y una terraza con vistas al mar. Goza de mucha luz y es alegre.

The space
Goza de una situacion privilegiada, en el centro de Palamós delante del mar y el puerto. La terraza con vistas a toda la bahia, es un placer para la vista.
Precios de Mayo y Junio: 400 euros por semana. Precio en Julio y Agosto: 500 euros por semana.

Guest access
Playa, paseos por el paseo marítimo, puerto, frente a la oficina de turismo, restaurantes, bares, boley-playa, buceo, alquiler de bicicletas, centros para conectarse a internet.

name: Luxury house in green oasis, huge pool, fab views!
description:
This is a spacious house with uninterrupted views of the stunning Mediterranean for people who want fun and exploration but value comfort and relative peace when they get back from their excursions.

It is light, spacious and very comfortable, with a/c, high speed, unlimited wifi and well-equipped kitchen.

The shared pool is very large - for swimming in, not splashing, and never crowded.

We use Maremar ourselves and want to keep it like a home. You will feel like our personal guests!

The space
Maremar is our holiday home not "a rental". Everything is designed with our own comfort in mind - from the extra comfortable beds and bedding to the A/C and unlimited wifi to the well equipped kitchen to the fact you will not have to go shopping for loo rolls and tea bags as soon as you arrive!

We have one of the largest houses in our community, which means you will not be cramped.

Our town is one of the very best on th
neighborhood_overview:
The beauty of Sant Feliu de Guixols is that it is a prosperous Catalan town visited by the well-healed of Barcelona and France. It is not a town that relies on packing visitors together like sardines and offering them a uniform touristic experience.

It has all of the best resort amenities but has not had to go "down market" to attract visitors and therefore attracts people who are genuinely interested in a Catalan experience (although the inhabitants do speak many languages).

You will have access to many beautiful coves, stunning beaches and all of that, but also history, first class gastronomy and fantastic art such as the three Salvador Dali properties.

You can spend the day on the beach or exploring the marina or the fishing port. You can enjoy first class shopping and night life. But then you can come "home" to relative peace and tranquility at Maremar.
host_about:
I am a semi retired company director and chartered accountant who has escaped to travel and have fun!

I love good company, food, wine, music, experiences and kind thoughtful people.

My wife and I delight in helping people to have really memorable holidays and experiences - we get a real buzz out of it!

name: Large family-an Apartment for an independent stay!
description:
Can Banal is a 16th century catalan farm house locally called masia that has been restored into three independent livings. During the summer we run a camp-site on the terraces below the main house.

The Terracotta Apartment...
· Is a 60 m2 large room, suitable max 7 persons – preferently a large family.
· There is a double bed (160cm), a bunk bed and a bed-sofa.
· The kitchen is equipped with gas cooking-stove, micro-wave and an extractor.
· It has a large furnished balcony with a pleasant view.
· Central heating and tv&wifi. There are all the facilities for an own supported stay (sheets, towels, kitchen-tools, household items)
· It is a good reunion room for medium size groups.
· The entrance to the house will be shared with us.

The landscape around Can Banal is in a rural and peaceful environment with rivers and forests that changes colors depending on the season. In autumn there are varieties of mushrooms and in spring many
neighborhood_overview:
Can Banal is situated in the beginning of the Catalan Pyrenees, in a region called “Alta Garrotxa”. Located midway between the sea-shore (45 min) and the high mountains of the Pyrenees (1h) makes it possible for many types of day-trips.
Close to many interesting places of cultural, natural or gourmet aspects like Castelfullit de la Roca, Besalu, the Garrotxa Volcanic Park or Olot.
Within a 6 km drive, Sadernes is reached from where the wonderful trekking path towards Sant Aniol d'Aguja starts.

The landscape around Can Banal is peaceful and rural, with rivers and forests that changes colours depending on the season. In autumn there are varieties of mushrooms and in spring many types of orquids and butterflies to enjoy.

If you just decides to stay around in Can Banal you'll find enough to do for few days. Walk our own signed trails along water creeks, fields, forests, hermitage, farms and villages round us. We have mountain bike’s to rent and in a 25' wal
host_about:
Hola, we are Stendert & Maria

We live in Mas Can Banal for many years. Stendert, born '51, originally is from Breda-Holland, and Maria, born '66, is from Stockholm-Sweden, where her parents once had arrived from Spain. We enjoy very much living here in the countryside surrounded by hills, forests, and rivers. Halfway to the sea and to the high mountains.

We are accompanied by our daughter Saskia born '02 and Stendert's son - Luuk, born  '93, who works in our village and in their spare time help us.

Our professions are of the most diverse; Maria studied interior design and artistic glass techniques and Stendert studied to become a tropical agronomist and later carpentry. Probably this multifaceted mixture connects us with many diverse interests and activities, especially the maintenance of CB with its forest, animals, and agro-tourism.

We hope to be able to combine these aspects of us and make your stay as pleasant and memorable as possible. Together, we speak 7 European languages and understand a few more. We like very much to tell you about our favorite places, help you out for more personal advice and add if there is a special event going on.

  Welcome·Bienvenidos·Welkom·Benvinguts·Välmommen·Bienvenue·Willkommen

Hola somos Maria and Stendert

Vivimos en Mas Can Banal desde hace muchos años. Stendert, nacido '51, originario de Breda , Holanda y María, nacida '66, de Estocolmo- Suecia , donde sus padres una vez llegaron desde España . Nos gusta mucho vivir aquí en el campo, rodeado de colinas, bosques y ríos. A mitad de camino hacia el mar y la mitad del camino a las altas montañas.

Nos acompaña nuestra hija Saskia, nacida '02 y Luuk, hijo de Stendert,  nacido en el '93, que trabaja en nuestro pueblo. Ambos en sus ratos libres nos ayudan en diferentes tareas.

Nuestras profesiones son de la más diversa; María estudió diseño de interiores y técnicas de vidrio artístico y Stendert estudió para ser ingeniero agrónomo tropical y mas tarde carpintería. Probablemente esta mezcla multifacética , nos conecta con muchos diversos intereses y actividades, en especial el mantenimiento de CB con su bosque, los animales y el agroturismo.

Esperamos ser capaces de combinar estos aspectos de nosotros y como hacer que su estancia sea lo más agradable y memorable como sea posible. En conjunto, se habla 7 idiomas europeos y entender algunos pocos más. Nos gusta mucho que decir acerca de nuestros lugares favoritos, ayudará a cabo el asesoramiento más personal y añadir si hay un evento especial ocurre.

name: Casa unifamiliar en el Valle de La Cerdanya
description:
La limpieza de la vivienda se realiza según recomendaciones de las autoridades sanitarias
Nuestra casa, típica vivienda del pirineo catalán, está situada el pequeño pueblo de Guils con increíbles vistas al valle de la Cerdanya, con su espectacular iglesia románica del Siglo XIV. Cerca de diferentes estaciones de esquí, españolas, francesas y andorranas. Y a pocos minutos de la estación de esquí de fondo Guils-Fontanera.

The space
Esta vivienda unifamiliar de dos plantas y con jardín privado, es un lugar muy agradable para familias con niños que les gusta la tranquilidad de la montaña y la práctica de deportes al aire libre.
Está ubicada dentro del pequeño municipio de Guils, en el Valle de La Cerdanya, muy cerca de diferentes estaciones de esquí, españolas, francesas y andorranas. Y a pocos minutos de la estación de esquí de fondo Guils-Fontanera..
Se accede desde la calle Muntanya por el garaje, en la planta inferior, o por el jardín entrando d
neighborhood_overview:
El pequeño municipio de Guils de Cerdanya está situado en los Pirineos gerundenses, en el valle de La Cerdanya, cuya capital es Puigcerdá, en la que el viajero encontrará todos los servicios, tales como tiendas, Hospital, cines, etc.
Guils de Cerdanya es un pueblo pequeño y muy tranquilo. Solo hay un restaurante, El Picarol, que abre los fines de semana, en Navidad y durante el mes de agosto. La estación de esquí nórdico Guils-Fontanera pertenece al municipio, y se accede por la carretera que sube desde Puigcerdá.
host_about:
Soy ingeniero de profesión, lo que hace que sea muy meticuloso y perfeccionista. Soy extrovertido, me encanta conocer nuevas gentes y culturas de las que aprendo muchas cosas.
Una de mis pasiones es viajar, que comparto con mi mujer. Juntos hemos visitado muchas de las hermosas ciudades europeas. Me encanta conocer mundo, soy un enamorado del continente africano, he viajado por diferentes países de ese continente.
Practico varios deportes pero sobre todo que sean al aire libre: esquí, tenis y golf, pero mi gran pasión es la pesca a mosca.
Me encanta el cine, las obras maestras las veo varias veces para no perder los detalles, y la lectura de novelas.

description:
Apartamento a primera línea de mar, muy luminoso y acogedor, ideal para parejas, hay otra mini habitación con una litera, hay un lavabo con bañera. La estancia mínima es de 5 días.

The space
Tiene vistas al mar y al río Muga que es una zona de reserva natural de l'empurdá, las vistas son impresionantes, el piso es muy luminoso y se encuentra a 50m de la playa y paseo marítimo

Other things to note
se pueden hacer paseos en barquita por los canales,de nuestra pequeña venecia,paseos en bici y si eres mas atrevido y te gusta el riesgo saltos de paracaidismo,anímate es muy divertido. Y la novedad túnel de viento y sino simplemente,relax,sol y playa y a disfrutar de las vacaciones

name: 10th century medieval Castle
description:
In the Ripollès region, between rivers, valleys and mountains, the ancient Castle of Llaés (10th century) stands splendidly. A unique place, of exceptional beauty, where absolute tranquility reigns in the middle of an exuberant nature.
The Castle has been fully renovated for the comfort required by the facilities for rural tourism, with 8 rooms, 5 with a double bed, and 3 with two single beds. It has a living room, dining room, kitchen, 4 bathrooms, garden and terrace.

The space
The Llaés Castle is a project of reform and maintenance of this national cultural asset that, by force of spirit and the guests from all over the world who come to visit us, can continue its journey.

Guest access
Currently the fortification retains the physiognomy of a castle, the homage tower, the parade ground, and the religious enclosure with a garden area, the small cemetery, and the church of San Bartolomé, in a marked Romanesque style.

Other
neighborhood_overview: In the town of Llaés we are 12 inhabitants, and what we like the most about our neighborhood, the tranquility and harmony that is breathed, the green of the mountains with the contrast of the electric blue of the sky. We love quiet afternoons where just looking up you see eagles, owls at dusk, butterflies, hares, moles, foxes, and countless more neighbors running around the neighborhood!
host_about:
Hello!
 We love the rural environment and the variety of activities offered: hiking, mountain biking, climbing, and a lot more.
We are fortunate to be able to receive people from all over the world in this small and incredible X century castle.
Always there, 24 hours 7 days a week, we ensure that our guests feel like royalty!
 We hope you have the best experience during your stay :) Marc & Ginny

Hola!
  Somos una pareja joven, amamos el entorno rural y la variedad de actividades que ofrece: senderismo, ciclismo de montaña, escalada y mucho más.
  ¡Somos afortunados de poder recibir personas de todo el mundo en este pequeño e increíble castillo del siglo X!
  Siempre allí, las 24 horas, los 7 días de la semana, nos aseguramos de que nuestros huéspedes se sientan como la realeza.
  ¡Esperamos que tengas la mejor experiencia durante tu estancia! :) Marc y Ginny

name: BEGUR. Country house in Costa Brava
description:
Restored house from 1.870 in the center of Begur one of the most beatiful villages in Costa Brava.

The space
The house was an old little factory to produce corks for wine bottles. It was refurbished as a summer residence for our family and friends.
We kept all the old elements from the past, old Catalonian ceiling, wooden doors, and old tile floors, opening big windows to make the place special and full of sun and light.
We love cooking, so the kitchen is perhaps bigger than normal, with all the equipment to prepare fresh food just bought in the local farmers.
It has a little garden of about 25m2. A special place to relax under the shadow of a jacaranda tree which gives flowers once a year (in June).

Guest access
The house was fully prepared as a summer residence 4 years ago. You will find 3 double rooms with two double beds and a double bunk. One of the rooms 100% independent on the lower floor close to the garden like a
neighborhood_overview: This is a quite pedestrian street with just one entrance. Only 5 lovely houses, our is the coziest one ;) . Good relationship with our neighbourhood, you will feel like a local soon. Some British, Spanish, Welch...
host_about:
...Life is short so I feel I need time to enjoy it as much as possible: lot of energy and creativity, the best friend of my friends, and a father 100% love.
Thus our house is always plenty of good friends who likes enjoying the good life that Costa Brava offers us, love wine, cooking, running  and staying on the beach till the sun goes down everyday.
...Dicen que la vida es corta. Es por eso que la quiero vivir tanto como pueda. Me considero positivo, creativo, el mejor amigo de mis amigos, y un padre envidiable con mi hijas.
Es por esto, que nuestra casa está siempre llena de buena gente, que le gusta la buena cocina, el buena vida en general, el deporte, aprovechar las puestas de sol para despedir el dia...y dar gracias al que está por llegar....

name: Céntrico y familiar
description:
Céntrico apartamento de 3 habitaciones y 2 baños. En el centro de Roses. Ubicado a 3' de la playa principal. En la misma calle, todo tipo de comercios y restaurantes. Climatizado y con doble cristal, optimo para el descanso. Dispone de ascensor, TV. y Wifi. Cocina de lujo, grande y bien equipada, con nevera, horno, vitro, microondas, lavavajillas, cafetera y tostadora. En un cuartito, todo para la perfecta colada, lavadora, y plancha de ropa.

The space
El apartamento se encuentra en pleno centro de Roses, pero en un barrio tranquilo para el descanso. a 200 metros de la playa de arena de Roses, así como del puerto y paseo marítimo. A 5 minutos a pie de toda la zona más turística si os apetece.
Es un apartamento nuevo con todas las comodidades.
3 habitaciones, una de ellas con el cuarto de baño incorporado tipo suite.
Espacios amplios y diáfanos. Completamente exterior. Climatizado frio y calor
Se trata de un edificio pequeño y familiar, 2º piso
neighborhood_overview:
Vecindario tranquilo, con varios comercios y restaurantes cercanos.
En la misma calle hay de todo, frutería, carnicería, pescadería, panadería, así como varios supermercados cercanos.
Hay una plaza de juegos infantiles en el mismo barrio.
host_about:
Mi prioridad es que los huéspedes se encuentren a gusto en mis apartamentos.
guardando la esencia de Airbnb.
Desde siempre, damos una especial atención a la limpieza e higiene, ahora más, ajustándonos a los protocolos marcados por el ICTE.
Roses es la ubicación ideal para una extensa variedad de actividades por toda la zona.
Gracias por confiar en mí ! Espero conocerte!

name: Nice studio vintage in Old Town
description:
Our cozy studio is equipped with everything you need to feel comfortable during your stay. It's an ideal place for couples, located in the old city center, near the main tourist attractions and the best restaurants

Due to the current situation, caused by COVID-19, we have taken extreme higienic measures to clean and disinfect in order to avoid any risk of infection and we have installed a remote system that will allow you to dispose of the key autonomously, without to have physical contact.

The space
First of all, we want to tell you that our studio is located on the first floor without a lift, so when you arrive, you will have to climb about 15 steps.

Once inside, you will see that the distribution consists of an open space with living room, dining room, office and kitchen, a bathroom and an attic with a double bed.

The balcony is a viewpoint of one of the most emblematic streets in the city. Here you can spend pleasant moments r
neighborhood_overview:
The studio is located in the old town, exactly in the historic center of Girona (Cort reial street). It is a charming area, close to the major historical sites and museums as well as the best restaurants in town.

At two minutes walking there is a supermarket where you can find all that you can need to cook your meals.

On the other hand, is a 10 minutes walk from the shopping area of the city and the bus and rail station. Do not forget that Girona has great attractions as a city, but it is also the starting point for visiting other inescapable places as the Costa Brava, the Dali Museum in Figueres, the charming villages of the Empordà or the Pirineus. As well, high-speed rail takes you in Barcelona in only 30'.
host_about:
Hello! 
We are Jaume and Marta. We live with our children in a small village half an hour from Girona, where we enjoy nature and peace of mind. 
We work as professor and librarian and we like to travel and discover curious and original spaces at the places we visit. 
We invite you to enjoy the small studio we have in the historic center of Girona and we promise to share with you everything we know of the city to make your stay very special and memorable.

name: stunning villa on the costa brava,
description:
Located on the most beautiful part of the Costa Brava, Vila Gelida has it all. A guesthouse for 3 downstairs, a private elevator to take you up to the mainhouse where the views are simply stunning, and the swimming pool awaits you. PermitHUTG- 009961.

The space
Enjoy lounging on one the terraces, by the pool, in the comfortable living room. Wherever you go, the Mediteranean sea follows you. Villa Gelida is decorated in modern style with some Asian touches.

License number
HUTG-009961
neighborhood_overview: Overlooking the impressive coast line of Aigua Blava and Begur and very close to the town of Tamariu, Villa Gelida is in a very unique location. Girona and Barcelona are an easy drive away. Numerous excellent golf courses are nearby, not to mention a huge choice of excellent and well priced restaurants. The waters in front of the house are among the best diving waters of the Coast, and you can rent gear or join a diving school in Tamariu. Boat rental is available in Tamariu.The famous Dali museum in Figueres is an hour's drive.
host_about:
This is our little piece of heaven..... It is our second home and we drive down as many weekends and holidays as possible from Barcelona. We have all traveled most of our lives and that would be a very important factor to the whole family, the need to travel and see and discover as much as possible. Part of the family spent many years in italy and the other part of the family in Asia.

5 things i would not be without, would be my family, recycling, animals,nature and the sea.
I love Jazz and Clasical music and love to read history books!

neighborhood_overview:
Begur is a typical, small town that started out as a fishing village. It is the proud location of some of the prettiest bays on the Mediterranean coast, all offering the crystalline water and pine forests that have made the Costa Brava famous. This area is also known for its many medieval towns, some of which (e.g. Peratallada) were declared historical and artistic monuments in 1975. In addition to the many small coves (Aigua Blava, Aigua Feda, Aigua Gélida, Sa Tuna, Fornells, etc.), Begur also has excellent sandy beaches (Sa Riera, Playa Pals, etc.) and even a nudist beach – the red island. There are many picturesque coastal towns that are worth a visit such as Calella de Palafrugell and Tamariu, and attractive harbours such as Llafranc.

The ruins of Begur castle offer one of the Costa Brava’s most spectacular views. The castle was the scene of pirate attacks that led the local inhabitants to turn their village away from the sea. The towers they built in the 16th and 17th

neighborhood_overview:

name: BAIX EMPORDÀ Rustic house rental
description:
This is your ideal home if you are looking for a quiet and wonderful landscape of Empordà without wanting to skip the easy access to the beaches of the Costa Brava. St Martí d'Empuries is 15 min. away and the Medes Islands not more than 20 min.

The space
It is an ideal house to enjoy with the family. It allows you to host very comfortably up to 7 people. Personally, I consider it important to note that one of the bedrooms, and a bathroom with shower, are located on the ground floor of the house (see the plans!)
On the other hand, from the garden and the lounge you have direct access to the porch leading to the garden.

In connection with its geographical location, it’s the perfect place if you want to enjoy a holiday in a quiet, rural location without giving up your daily swim on the beaches of the Costa Brava.

Furthermore! If you practice the golf, Golf or Pitch & Putt Golf Empordà and Pitch & Putt Gualta are just 15 minutes away.
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is a very quiet and perfectly located place near the beaches of St. Martí d'Empuries, L'Escala and Estartit. It's also a spot with easy and convenient access.
host_about:
Soy nacido en el Empordà, en la población de Palafrugell, y actualmente tengo 42 años.

Vivo en La Bisbal d'Empordà, con Silvia, mi compañera y con Mel, Maui y Bruno, nuestras mascotas.

Me licencié en Derecho en el año 2000 pero nunca he ejercido la profesión; seguramente, porqué prefiero la tranquilidad de la vida en mi tierra que teñir mi existencia con las tensiones de los Tribunales ( no estoy hecho para esto ).

En Airbnb anunciamos casas de la familia ( 2 casas en Canet de La Tallada y dos apartamentos en Palau-Sator ) y también otra casa cuyos derechos de explotación he adquirido ( Sant Iscle d'Empordà ).

El proyecto inicial de las casas de Canet de la Tallada era la venta pero la depresión del sector inmobiliario hizo a la familia cambiar de opinión y decidimos su explotación en modo de arrendamiento. Además, cuando no están alquiladas las usamos la familia ( somos 5 hermanos ).

En Palau-Sator, los apartamentos que tienen origen en la rehabilitación de la casa de mis abuelos paternos. Era una casa muy grande y hace ya más de 15 años la familia tomó la decisión de restaurara en este sentido.

Después de 3 años en la plataforma, mi experiencia como anfitrión con Airbnb es francamente buena. Salvo pequeños detalles y algún caso aislado estamos muy contentos con los huéspedes que nos han llegado.

Recomiendo el Empordà de forma enérgica, cualquiera de sus rincones, espacios, paisajes o playas...Esta región, es muchísimo más que el conocido Triángulo de Oro. Os lo aseguro!! 

Aquí, puedes relajarte, divertirte, ir de fiesta, en globo, practicar equitación, bajar en canoa por el río Ter, alquilar un velero, ir en bici, jugar a Golf o Picht&Putt, practicar nudismo, bañarte en calas preciosas o, si lo prefieres, en playas kilométricas, perderte en largos paseos al atarceder y comerte un buen arroz!!

name: Habitación doble en La Trobada Hotel Ripoll
description:
Somos un hotel familiar, con historia y de alta calidad. Estamos ubicados en el centro de Ripoll, sobre el río Ter, a 2 minutos a pie del Monasterio, a 5 minutos de la estación de trenes y autobuses, y con aparcamiento gratuito justo en frente.

The space
Nuestras habitaciones dobles superiores han sido totalmente remodeladas con el objetivo de ofrecer un espacio perfecto para nuestros clientes. Equipadas con una cama doble o dos camas individuales, cuentan con un cálido suelo de parquet y ropa de cama de algodón. Asimismo, los baños han sido diseñados pensando en el máximo confort, para ello cuentan con una amplia ducha o bañera de fácil acceso. Disponen de un escritorio preparado para para las nuevas tecnologías. Debido a su buena relación calidad-precio, las habitaciones dobles superiores son nuestras habitaciones más populares.

License number
HG-002103
neighborhood_overview:
Ripoll y El Ripollès, punto de nacimiento y confluencia de los Ríos Ter y Freser, es ideal para diferentes actividades de naturaleza y cultura.
En este sentido, cabe destacar la Vía Verde Ruta del Hierro y del Carbón, que comienza en el mismo paseo del hotel, la puerta principal del monasterio de Ripoll, ahora candidata al reconocimiento como Patrimonio Mundial de la UNESCO, el Museo Etnográfico de Ripoll,
y nuestra querida Vall de Núria. Somos buenos conocedores de nuestro territorio y estaremos encantados de recomendar a nuestros clientes los mejores lugares y actividades dirigidas y libres según sus intereses.
host_about:
Soy Jaume Farrés. Nací y crecí en La Trobada, el hotel que fundó mi abuelo junto con mi abuela y mi madre durante los años ochenta en Ripoll, en pleno corazón del Pirineo Catalán. Estudié arquitectura en Girona, preciosa ciudad donde viví seis años. Mi pasión por el hoquei patines, deporte me ha acompañado toda mi vida, me llevó a vivir en Barcelona durante dos años más. Ahora vivo de nuevo en Ripoll, en el hotel de mi familia. Combino mi profesión, arquitectura, con el negocio familiar, y el hoquei sobre patines. 

Me interesa el contraste entre lo local y lo global, y me gusta ser el anfitrión de los viajeros que llegan a Ripoll. 

Si quereis hacer excursiones, a pie o en bicicleta, os daré detalles de varias rutas que conozco perfectamente, y os recomendaré una u otra según vuestras preferencias!

The apartment is situated in a quiet residential area just outside Estartit and is only a short distance from many attractions that the area offers.

neighborhood_overview: The Costa Brava has a wealth of wonderful places and cuisine for the visitor to experience.  The area has some of the most beautiful beaches and hidden coves in Europe, for guests to explore.  There is an unlimited amount of water sports from kayaking, boat hire, windsurfing/boarding and other water-borne sports.  The Illes Medes islands, just off the coast of Estartit, is a protected marine area and has some of the best diving experiences in the Mediterranean.  Examples of occupying civilisations from the ancient Iberians to the Greeks and Romans have all left their mark on the landscape of this area.  There are great cycling routes and for the more tranquil pursuits, there are wonderful walks and bird watching opportunities.  The area also has a wealth of wonderful historical buildings/architecture for guests who wish to explore the history and culture. Cadaquès, beautiful little harbour,with Cap de Creus,beautiful natural park are just half an hour drive.
Welcome.

Casa Rabos is a traditional 17th century stone house, entirely renovated with all modern amenities and it is situated between Figueres and Llanca/Rosas near Perelada in north Catalonia, Spain.
The Orlina river runs down the village,and a beautiful bridgeunder which you can bathe.

Perched in the renowned bay of Rosas close to the sea and entoured on one side by the Pyrenee mountains with 3,000 meter snowcapped summits. The climate is ideal with more than 300 days of sunshine per y
neighborhood_overview:
The house is on the outskirts of a charming medieval village at the foot of which the Orlina river flows.
The village is very peaceful, it has a small grocery store open in the morning only.
You can take beautiful walks, discover dolmens and menhirs in the middle of the surrounding garrigue, located in the Albera natural park.
host_about:
D'origine Québecoise, je m'occupe de cette merveilleuse maison de famille qui a au dessus de 400 ans ,et dans laquelle on fabriquait autrefois l'huile d'olive, le pain et le vin.
 Je partage cette occupation avec ma mère qui elle,est catalane d'origine et vit au Québec une grande partie de l'année.
J'ai suivi une formation en tourisme et aime partager ma passion pour la vie.
  Ma mère ,elle ,est massothérapeuthe et enseigne le Qi Gong, elle donne des ateliers d'initiation de cet art.
  Nous aimons toutes les deux recevoir les gens, qu'ils se sentent à l'aise et chaleureusement accueillis.
  Nous aimons aussi la nature, les plantes, la musique, la mer, la montagne, avoir du plaisir et partager tous ces merveilleux cadeaux que nous donne la vie;

neighborhood_overview: La vila de Ripoll se encuentra en un espacio natural privilegiado, ríos y montañas invitan al viajero a conocerles. El románico está muy presente en nuestra comarca, varios municipios cuentan con puente o iglesia románica. El monasterio de Santa María de Ripoll es destacable por su gran peso histórico y cultural.
host_about:
Soy Jaume Farrés. Nací y crecí en La Trobada, el hotel que fundó mi abuelo junto con mi abuela y mi madre durante los años ochenta en Ripoll, en pleno corazón del Pirineo Catalán. Estudié arquitectura en Girona, preciosa ciudad donde viví seis años. Mi pasión por el hoquei patines, deporte me ha acompañado toda mi vida, me llevó a vivir en Barcelona durante dos años más. Ahora vivo de nuevo en Ripoll, en el hotel de mi familia. Combino mi profesión, arquitectura, con el negocio familiar, y el hoquei sobre patines. 

Me interesa el contraste entre lo local y lo global, y me gusta ser el anfitrión de los viajeros que llegan a Ripoll. 

Si quereis hacer excursiones, a pie o en bicicleta, os daré detalles de varias rutas que conozco perfectamente, y os recomendaré una u otra según vuestras preferencias!

name: Charming Seaside Family Home, 2 Min Walk to Beach
description:
Our eclectic, charming family home is located in a picturesque vibrant seaside village, just a couple of minute's walk from the fabulous local beaches. Situated in the "old-town" centre, our townhouse retains original features e.g. patterned ceramic floor tiles, vaulted ceilings & characteristic window shutters. You'll benefit from the "home from home" (as in family home/not a hotel!) atmosphere while immersing yourself in village life, with an array of cafes & bars on your doorstep. Enjoy :)

The space
Our home is located in the "old town" of L'Escala, a former fishing village, on the beautiful Costa Brava. This is not a hotel style rental but rather it is our family home.

The accommodation is situated over three floors, with kitchen and dining room on the ground floor. The 4 bedrooms (one with kingsize bed and 3 with single beds) and the WC and bathroom are found on the middle floor. The sitting room is located on the top floor and leads onto
neighborhood_overview:
The house is situated in a peaceful residential area in the "old town" of L'Escala, close to several beaches. The sandy family beach, surrounded by a variety of cafes and restaurants, is located just beyond the bottom of our road. A short stroll away are a number of independent boutiques, jewellery and craft shops, also shops selling local Anchovies of L'Escala. Creu Cove, a minute's walk away (to the left of our house), is great for snorkelling. The larger, sandy crescent beaches of Empúries are a short walk away, and if you want a bit of culture you can visit the nearby Greco-Roman ruins of Empúries. Also within walking distance (a bit of a hike, but worth the walk!), along the beautiful scenic coastal path, is Sant Marti d'Empúries, a charming hill top hamlet with a selection of fabulous restaurants, overlooking the Golf of Roses.

If you drive, there is free parking in our street but the residents use the spaces so you will most likely have to park your car at the to
host_about:
Hello from Seeta and John!

I'm an editor and John is an architect who undertook the renovations on our house which hadn't been lived in for 40 years.  We hope you will enjoy our home as much as we do :)

description:
Casa con chimenea , patio privado y piscina compartida.
Cal Ouaire ofrece una experiencia auténtica en el corazón del Empordà. Se trata de una casa restaurada, rodeada de bosques y pequeñas casas que conforman el tranquilo barrio de Diana. El edificio un antiguo pajar se ha reformado con la premisa de preservar su estructura original como sus paredes de piedra, buscando siempre serenidad y confort. El resultado no es más que un hogar tranquilo que transmite una sensación de simplicida...

The space
Cal Ouaire es una masia Catalana restaurada rodeada de pequeñas casas que conforman el tranquilo vecindario de Diana.
El edificio ha sido renovado a partir de la ruina de una antigua granja. Las renovaciones se llevaron a cabo con las premisas de preservar sus paredes de piedra, buscando siempre la serenidad y comodidad. El resultado no es más que un hogar tranquilo que transmite una sensación de simplicidad y calma. La casa está amueblada con un estilo na
neighborhood_overview:
Todo se reduce a una experiencia sencilla y pura. Huimos de las aglomeraciones y buscamos la discreción. Queremos que nuestros huéspedes formen parte de esta tierra, la vivan y la disfruten de una forma especial. Buscamos ser parte del recuerdo que te llevarás.
La desconexión y el descanso lo encontramos en una puesta de sol, en el ruido de los árboles, en el aire y la energía del viento del Empordà.La casa está emplazada en un camino a 2 kilómetros de Sant Jordi Desvalls. Es un lugar donde reina la tranquilidad y el silencio. Un precioso paisaje de interior, rodeado de campos, huertos y bosques donde disfrutar de agradables paseos.
A escasos kilómetros de la casa se encuentran las playas más bonitas de la Costa Brava. A tan sólo 20 minutos en coche de l'Estartit, i l'Escala, y a 25 minutos de Girona. También podrás visitar numerosos pueblos con encanto. En la casa encontraríes varias ediciones de la Guia de l'Empordà y recomandaciones.
En el pueblo de Sant Jordi Desva
host_about:
Nuestra familia siempre trabajó en el campo y nuestra ilusión de dar nueva vida a antiguos espacios utilizados para el ganado y sus cultivos nos llevaron a construir estas magníficas casas, respetando siempre el entorno y los lugares, con materiales honestos y de calidad.. 
Estaremos encantados de daros la bienvenida y explicaros lo que creemos es lo mejor y más bonito de la zona del Empordà y el Gironès.

name: Rustic apartment near beaches and golf courses
description:
Located at the characteristic medieval village of Palau-Sator, this renovated apartment offers you a comfortable residency during your holidays. The living room, dining room, and kitchen merge into a single open-plan space, painted in warm tones and filled with light. Totally furnished, the living room area is fitted out with two sofas, a coffee table and, for your entertainment, a flat screen TV and Wi-Fi service.
The apartment offers also two bedrooms and one bathroom.

The space
This specific location, which is setteld in a very quiet medieval village is an exceptional catalan

Guest access
The apartment has no public areas. All spaces, interior and exterior, are strictly for private use. Wifi.

Other things to note
As for the tourist accommodation tax, upon arrival, you will be charged the amount of € 0.45 / per person over 16 years / night (up to 7 nights).

Minimum 7 nights from Saturday to Saturday
neighborhood_overview: Historic center of Palau-Sator, medieval village in the province of Girona. Located 10-15 minutes from the beaches of the Costa Brava (Pals, Begur, Estartit..). Palau-Sator, is a quiet tourist town. You will not find large crowds. The neighbours, mostly, are people from the country. It is also important to note that in the village there are exactly 4 restaurants, I particularly recommend Can Saló and Mas Pou.
host_about:
Soy nacido en el Empordà, en la población de Palafrugell, y actualmente tengo 42 años.

Vivo en La Bisbal d'Empordà, con Silvia, mi compañera y con Mel, Maui y Bruno, nuestras mascotas.

Me licencié en Derecho en el año 2000 pero nunca he ejercido la profesión; seguramente, porqué prefiero la tranquilidad de la vida en mi tierra que teñir mi existencia con las tensiones de los Tribunales ( no estoy hecho para esto ).

En Airbnb anunciamos casas de la familia ( 2 casas en Canet de La Tallada y dos apartamentos en Palau-Sator ) y también otra casa cuyos derechos de explotación he adquirido ( Sant Iscle d'Empordà ).

El proyecto inicial de las casas de Canet de la Tallada era la venta pero la depresión del sector inmobiliario hizo a la familia cambiar de opinión y decidimos su explotación en modo de arrendamiento. Además, cuando no están alquiladas las usamos la familia ( somos 5 hermanos ).

En Palau-Sator, los apartamentos que tienen origen en la rehabilitación de la casa de mis abuelos paternos. Era una casa muy grande y hace ya más de 15 años la familia tomó la decisión de restaurara en este sentido.

Después de 3 años en la plataforma, mi experiencia como anfitrión con Airbnb es francamente buena. Salvo pequeños detalles y algún caso aislado estamos muy contentos con los huéspedes que nos han llegado.

Recomiendo el Empordà de forma enérgica, cualquiera de sus rincones, espacios, paisajes o playas...Esta región, es muchísimo más que el conocido Triángulo de Oro. Os lo aseguro!! 

Aquí, puedes relajarte, divertirte, ir de fiesta, en globo, practicar equitación, bajar en canoa por el río Ter, alquilar un velero, ir en bici, jugar a Golf o Picht&Putt, practicar nudismo, bañarte en calas preciosas o, si lo prefieres, en playas kilométricas, perderte en largos paseos al atarceder y comerte un buen arroz!!

name: Edirla
description:
Es la primera de nuestras habitaciones. Situada en la planta baja de la casa y con salida directa a la fachada principal. Orientada al sur, es una habitación fresca en verano y cálida en invierno.

The space
En el exterior puedes disfrutar del bar, la piscina, los rincones sorprendentes, y el paisaje excepcional que rodea la casa. Las fantásticas playas de Pals se encuentran a 20 minutos andando y el núcleo antiguo de Pals o el nucleo cercano de Begur a pocos minutos en bicicleta por caminos interiores de gran belleza.
La masía está situada en un entorno ideal para conocer la zona de Pals y el bajo empordán, donde se suceden los pequeños pueblos medievales y las playas de la Costa Brava. name: Beautiful old farmhouse with pool II  (PG-502)
description:
Mas Vinyoles is at the same time away from it all and close to everything: Beach, mountains, beautiful cities like Girona, Barcelona, Figueres.... After a full and busy day it is wonderfull to retire to it's unique quietness.

The space
Mas Vinyoles is a Catalan countryside house that is partly converted to offer a pleasant space to spend your holidays: 2 fully equipped apartments, for 4 and 6 people.
There is a garden with a swimming pool and bbq, a biological vegetable garden and an orchard.
We are in the heart of the protected area ″Les Gavarres ″, a series of hills of Mediterranean forest between Girona and Costa Brava.
This is a place to spend some quiet days of rest, exploring the surroundings by foot or on bicycle.

Guest access
Guests will have access to the swimming pool (sea salt water), a beautiful garden surrounding the house, tons of hills with cork trees, silence, bird songs and clean sky with outstanding stars.
neighborhood_overview: We are 33 neighbours in the middle of a protected wooden area.
host_about: I live in "Les Gavarres" since 1985 and I love it. To take care of the forest and the wild life has become an important project of my life. I am happy to realise that every year a new variety of birds discover that this is a good place for them to spend at least part of the year.

60km from Perpingnan (France)

Girona in 15 minutes

Som parella desde fa uns anys, francesa ella, català jo, ella treballa en el sector de salud, el meu en el sector de telecomunicacions.

Viatgem on podem quan podem, ens desplacem fent cicloturisme, amb autocaravana, o caminant, sempre tot és millor caminant plegats!!!

Aficionats al "make your self", som uns bojos del brico! tenim el nostre propi hortet, fem la nostre mermelada, recollim plantes remeires...

neighborhood_overview: Tous commerces d'alimentation, petits supermarchés, pharmacie, tabac, journaux (catalan), coiffure, nombreux restaurants, cafés, pizzerias et crêperies à proximité - La plupart ouverts le dimanche matin - Un commerce de plats à emporter ouvert le dimanche toute la journée - Un commerce de boisson, alimentation de base et produits de nécessité ouvert le dimanche toute la journée l'été - Supermarché Charter Consum ouvert toute la journée non-stop y compris lundi - Parc situé à 200 mètres pour activités ludiques, sportives ou de détente, barbecue et piscine -
host_about: Musicien classique (instrumentiste à cordes interprète) passionné de sports outdoor, hiking et alpinisme (ski), sports de raquettes (tennis, padel,etc.), golf et voile - A fait de Llivia et de la Cerdagne son "centre d'entraînement en altitude" - Simple, discret, accueillant et très heureux de faire profiter son appartement qui peut se prêter aussi bien à un esprit familial et de détente qu'à des activités orientées outdoor et montagne ou enfin à une recherche de calme et de tranquilité -

neighborhood_overview:
GPS Coordenades: 42.034452554751766, 2.9899871349334717

Can Carrió is located in the northern part of Foixà, in the neighbourhood of Cuells, in a residential zone surrounded by fields and pine and oak woodland which give a magical air of tranquillity.

4Km away is the Gala/Dali foundation in Púbol Castle, vertex of the Dali triangle with Figueres and Port- Lligat. 35km away is the town of Figueres and the Museo Dalí.

20 Km from Foixà are the beaches of Empúries, Escala, Estartit and Pals, and the Costa Brava stretching out before you. Estartit offers an important base for Scuba diving in the protected surroundings of the Medes Islands. Also 20km away is the historic city of Girona.

Around the village there are different cycle routes and footpaths which allow you to explore the local area.

Pequeño estudio de 35m2 con capacidad para dos plazas, totalmente reformado conservando el estilo rustico, dispone de todos los servicios independientes (cocina, baño con ducha hidromasaje, chimenea, etc)

The space
Can Barrina, es una atigua casa Pairal situada en la plaza del fantástico pueblo de Ventalló, conocido por el encanto de sus calles y casas de piedra de estilo rustico.

La casa ha sido totalmente reformada en 2014 conservando su caracter y autenticidad.
En la segunda planta del edificio encontramos este pequeño estudio de un solo ambiente con una cama doble, un sofa cama y chimenea.Con un total de 2-4 plazas

Guest access
En la parte superior del edificio una amplia terraza desde dónde se puede ver todo el golf de rosas con el mar y las montañas del cap de Creus.
También se pone a disposición de los huéspedes una zona común de lavanderia

Other things to note
Botella de cava, vino, bombon
neighborhood_overview: Ventallo, es un precioso pueblo situado en pleno empordà, a tan solo 5 minutos de las playas en coche y muy cercano a los principales atractivos turísticos de la zona (aiguamolls de l'emporda, empuries, figueres y museo dali, etc)

name: Perfect place for beach holiday.
description:
Well maintained apartment on the beach and with sea view in Santa Margarita - Roses. It is located in front of the beach of Santa Margarita. From the vitrified terrace you have a beautiful sea view.

The space
Well maintained apartment on the beach and with sea view in Santa Margarita - Roses. Perfect place for beach holiday.
The apartment is on the 4th floor of the building Roses Holiday Centre on the northern Costa Brava in Roses - Santa Margarita.
It is located in front of the beach of Santa Margarita. From the vitrified terrace you have a beautiful sea view.
The apartment has a spacious living room with dining area, sleeping alcove with 2 single beds, and a separate bedroom with double bed. The kitchenette is equipped with a small fridge, a ceramic glass cooktop, oven and a filter coffee machine. Cutlery, crockery, pots and pans are also available. A bathroom with shower, a modern satellite TV and a washing machine complement the equipment. <
neighborhood_overview: sin registro
host_about: Seit 1987 lebe ich in Roses, meiner Wahlheimat. Ich liebe dieses Fleckchen Erde. In meiner Freizeit bewaffne ich mich oft mit unserem Hund Uma - eine Königspudeldame, die aber Hund sein darf,  und Fotoapparat und mache unsere Bucht "unsicher" :-), während meine Lebensgefährte Joan, gebürtiger "Rosinc" - so heissen die Bewohner aus Roses, mit dem Fahrrad unterwegs ist. Wir hoffen, Sie recht bald kennen zu lernen und wieder einen neuen "Roses-Fan" gewinnen zu können.
