name: Fidara
description:
Una habitación muy especial, situada en la planta baja. Cubierta de bóveda catalana, con salida directa a uno de los rincones más bellos del exterior de la casa, junto al pozo.

The space
En el exterior puedes disfrutar del bar, la piscina, los rincones sorprendentes, y el paisaje excepcional que rodea la casa. Las fantásticas playas de Pals se encuentran a 20 minutos andando y el núcleo antiguo de Pals o el nucleo cercano de Begur a pocos minutos en bicicleta por caminos interiores de gran belleza.
La masía está situada en un entorno ideal para conocer la zona de Pals y el bajo empordán, donde se suceden los pequeños pueblos medievales y las playas de la Costa Brava. En el área más cercana es posible además participar en gran variedad de actividades deportivas y culturales muy variadas: museos, festivales, senderismo, golf, deportes de agua etc. A menos de una hora, se puede visitar Torroella de Montgrí, Figueres, Girona o Perpinyá con toda su oferta cultura

name: House in 17th-century Villa, countryside and sea!
description:
Mas Blanc is a historical Villa built in 1611 in a unique location in Ullastret, Emporda, Costa Brava. Despite many years have gone through, the Villa still maintains its charming environment being completely surrounded by nature, a very special and peaceful refugee!

The space
The house is located in a unique and beautiful location in the area of Empordanet, very close to small rural and medieval villages and easy access to the beautiful beaches of Costa Brava. The closest villages are Ullastret, Peratallada, Palau - Sator, Gualta, Pals, Torroella, La Bisbal.

The nearest beaches are Pals, La Gola de Ter, Estartit, Begur, Calella de Palafrugell, Llafranc, Tamariu...

You can go biking to the beach or to visit these medieval and Iberian villages, and enjoy the delicious traditional restaurants in the area!

Guest access

The space
Spectacular design house of 258 m2 in a garden of 2060 m2 located in the Valle de Ribes, built in stone, wood and steel, its southern orientation provide you unbeatable views.

8, consists of a floor and attic, kitchen-dining-living room in one and airy feel, with three bedrooms, a king suite with full bath and wood stove, double (double) and one quadruple (ideal children ).

Three bathrooms warm and welcoming design, loft with chaselongue relaxing and desks. Wifi throughout the house, large flat television format, audio equipment.

Fantastic garden (2060 m2) private and intimate, ideal for lovers of relaxation, sport, tranquility, fami
neighborhood_overview:
Campelles is part of the Ripollès region, in the province of Girona.
It is a very well-preserved natural area with all kinds of fauna, ideal for short excursions along the river, with the option of bathing in its refreshing waters in summer. During the fall, it is a very good place to go looking for mushrooms, or in winter to ski on the nearby slopes of Vall de Núria, La Molina, Masella or Vallter 2000.The town also offers a great variety of local gastronomic products, they highlight its sausages and cheeses, honey or biscuits from Camprodon, near Campelles, are also highly appreciated.

name: El Sorrall 3. 1 bedroom apartment. Sea Views
description:
The ´Apartments El Sorrall´ are the type of apartments for clients who want to have a quiet or family holiday by the sea. A place for our clients to feel at ease. They are located in the quiet but touristic town of Blanes, in the Costa Brava. An ideal place to spend a family vacation by the sea and only a stone's throw away from the beach. All the apartments have a balcony with spectacular views of the promenade and beach.

The space
El Sorrall is a building with several types of apartments, in this case the one bedroom apartments are for two persons. The building has an elevator for easier access. There is a bedroom with 2 beds. Complete bathroom with sink, toilet , bidet and bath . Electric boiler for the hot water system. American Kitchen with refrigerator, two electric cooking hobs, extractor fan, microwave and sink. Dining room with sofa for three persons , table with three chairs and a flat screen TV. Balcony with a table and two chairs.
The apartments
neighborhood_overview: These apartments are only 300m away from the center of Blanes and its immediate surroundings and everyday facilities: supermarket, bakery, daily fruit and vegetable markets, butchers, and other small shops. Also, within the vicinity there are facilities such as a sports hall, children´s playground, parking, etc.

description:

Este confortable apartamento recientemente reformado, ubicado en la población pirenaica de Llivia, Valle de La Cerdanya y cerca de diferentes estaciones de esquí, españolas, francesas y andorranas.
Tiene tres habitaciones y dos baños con capacidad para 8 personas. El amplio salón comedor, con chimenea, está abierto a la cocina muy completa.

The space
Este amplio y luminoso apartamento está ubicado en un edificio, con zona común ajardinada y piscina, dentro de la pueblo de Llivia, en el Valle de La Cerdanya, cerca de diferentes estaciones de esquí, españolas, francesas y andorranas.
Es un lugar muy agradable para familias con niños que les gusta la tranquilidad de la montaña y la práctica de deportes al aire libre.
El apartamento ha sido recientemente reformado por completo. Tiene capacidad para 8 huéspedes. Al entrar a través del pasillo, encontramo
neighborhood_overview: El pueblo de Llivia está ubicado, en el valle de La Cerdanya, dentro del territorio francés, cerca de la antigua frontera entre España y Francia. Encontrará muchos de los servicios que precise tales como restaurantes, tiendas, la famosa farmacia de Llivia, etc. De todas formas, está a pocos kilómetros de Puigcerdá, la capital de la comarca.
host_about:
Soy ingeniero de profesión, lo que hace que sea muy meticuloso y perfeccionista. Soy extrovertido, me encanta conocer nuevas gentes y culturas de las que aprendo muchas cosas.
Una de mis pasiones es viajar, que comparto con mi mujer. Juntos hemos visitado muchas de las hermosas ciudades europeas. Me encanta conocer mundo, soy un enamorado del continente africano, he viajado por diferentes países de ese continente.
Practico varios deportes pero sobre todo que sean al aire libre: esquí, tenis y golf, pero mi gran pasión es la pesca a mosca.
Me encanta el cine, las obras maestras las veo varias veces para no perder los detalles, y la lectura de novelas.

Arrels d'Emporda cuenta con un bar y una sala de reuniones para alquilar. Hay un mercado de productos tradicionales a 500 metros de los apartamentos.

Hay varias playas de la Costa Brava a 10 minutos en coche. El aeropuerto de Girona está a 40 km y el establecimiento ofrece servicio de traslado.

description:
Our high standing apartment has beautiful views over the Bay of Roses. The apartment has 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms a large living room, and a terrace overlooking the Mediterranean.
The kitchen has all modern comforts. A garage for 2 cars is available

The space
The apartment has been recently renovated and has a high quality finish. It is situated on the 2nd floor of a small apartment block with swimming pool. Six people can easily be accommodated and we can provide a cot for small children and high chair. The views across the bay never gets boring. The terrace is large and has a dining corner and lounge chairs.

Guest access

may be some cupboards locked in the living room. They can use the swimming pool an
neighborhood_overview:
What do we love about Roses. I suppose the beautiful sea, the fishing fleet, which leaves port everyday to return in the late afternoon, which is a lovely sight from our terrace. The sunsets. The restaurants and the nice boulevard of Roses.
The nice villages to visit near Roses, such as Cadaques, Figueres with its Dali museum, the National Parks of Cap de Creus and Aiguamolls.
host_about:
Twenty five years ago we wanted to buy a house in France for our holidays and we found Le Coustal. We restored first the old farmhouse dated 1870 and this is the place we used to live in ourselves. Now this beautiful  farmhouse is also for rent and we named it La Ferme.  We ourselves moved to Château Preyssac in Thenon,  which we are renovating right now.  We started to restore all the other buildings on the domaine. Many years later we could buy the land of our neighbors and we were able to completely renovate the Maison de Maitre and opening it for guests six years ago. 
We are originally from the Netherlands, however 16 years ago we moved from Holland to the United Arab Emirates with our daughter Sanne. 
Nowadays I spend my time between France and the Emirates and together with my daughter Sanne and a dedicated team we take care of our guests in France and Spain, where we also have a family property ( las Rocas) hosted by my cousin Gijb.
Apart from las Rocas we now manage 3 more properties in Rosas: 
Belleza del Mar, Casa Diaz, and Casa Flamenco. 
in the future we hope to add some more treehouses at the domaine Lalande-Laborie. At the moment there are two and maybe in the future in the forests of Preyssac !!

host_about:
Soy una mujer servicial y hospitalaria. Me gusta que la gente se sienta cómoda y feliz a mi alrededor. Intento tratar a mis huéspedes como me gustaría que me trataran a mi. 
Me congratula compartir experiencias y una de ellas es ceder mi propiedad de Lloret de Mar para disfrute vacacional y de ocio.
En mi apartamento doy prioridad al confort, la limpieza, una buena dotación de equipamiento doméstico, servicios y un entorno íntimo y agradable para que tanto famílias como parejas disfruten de un alojamiento y estancia immejorable, relajante y placentera... Además, yo estoy siempre disponible presencial y/o telefónicamente por si hay cualquier problema.
Parece que consigo mi objetivo puesto que frecuentemente alojo inquilinos repetidores. Mi premio es ver las caras de mis clientes cuando se marchan (y vuelven!).
Esta es mi mayor satisfacción!

name: Appartement vue magnifique sur mer
description:
Dans une petite résidence de 2x7 appartements équipée d'une grande piscine centrale 10mx5m et parking privé.
Loue à la semaine du samedi 16 heures au samedi suivant 10 heures studio entièrement équipé pour 3 personnes avec magnifique terrasse de 3mx3m dominant toute la baie de Rosas. L'une des 30 plus belles baies du monde au classement de l'UNESCO.

The space
Studio très lumineux avec sa baie vitrée de 3 metres de large.
Carrelage gris clair au sol peinture blanche murs et plafond.

Guest access

D'ou la vue exceptionnelle ( voir les commentaires)

D'ou le calme , loin du brouhaha de la ville de Rosas bien que distante de seulement 2 kms.

Quartier très résidenciel.

name: Sleep & Stay deluxe aptmt old town
description:
Make your visit to Girona memorable staying in this fantastic deluxe apartment that is overlooking the main square of the town hall, Placa del Vi and on walking distance of all shops, restaurants and Jewish quarter.

We are looking forward hosting you in our beautiful medieval city!

The space
The apartment is beautifully decorated, with a spacious open dining, kitchen and living room with a super relaxing modern seating area featuring windows and balconies that overlook one of the main squares of the old town, Barri Vell.
The kitchen is recently renovated with all appliances needed and has plenty of kitchen wear. There's a Dolce Gusto coffee machine, oven, microwave, dishwasher, air-con and washing machine. In the living room there is a sofa bed for an extra 3rd and 4th guest.
There is one spacious double bedroom with a kingsize bed (160x200m) and lots of wardrobe space. The mattress is off a high quality, purchased in 2021 We provide high
neighborhood_overview: Located in Plaza del Vi,  this is the center of all cultural activities in Girona.  You'll have all markets, shops and landmarks walking 2 min away from the building.
host_about:
Sleep and Stay is a professional holiday rental agency and licensed Real estate Agency.
All our properties are carefully selected and we prioritize customer service, a personal touch and impecable cleaning. We leave a welcome package with cleaning products (dishwasher tablets, laundry tablets, sponge, cloth and extra garbage bags) and first essentials like coffee, tea, sugar, salt, pepper, olive oil and vinegar. Those items you just need for a couple of days away, are just great to have at your disposal. 
Most people that visit Girona once, never want to leave again. They want to come back, because Girona has it all. We recently opened a branch in Besalu which is small medieval copy of Girona. We have beaches, culture of Dali, the great Spanish kitchen with lot’s of different tapas and wines, old medieval villages and mountains great for skiing, hiking and cycling! What else do you want?

That’s why we fell in love with Girona and made it our business of helping people to find their dream holiday home for a week’s stay or even to buy a property and have a second home in this amazing region! Sleep & Stay is owned by Jolien Huizing Gerrans, Dutch nationality, and she has surrounded herself by an amazing team. Sonia (Polish) and Luis (Honduras). We personally manage each holiday property that are featured on this website and are experts in the Girona property market for more than 4 years. We all speak next to our mother tongues Spanish, Catalan and English which makes all language barriers disappear!

As a young and dynamic holiday rental organisation, specialised in amazing holiday rentals, property management and property finder services. We can assist you in finding a special place to stay in Girona. We value quality, comfort and well maintained holiday rentals as our most important goals. We want to find that charming place for you that makes you fall in love with Girona too and makes you want to stay forever.

Once you arrive and you need anything, we are here to help you. Available on (Hidden by Airbnb) , email and we're just a phone call away. Welcome to come and stay with us!

description:
El loft es un pequeño refugio para descansar, desconectar y relajarse. Un espacio único de planta baja con un diseño minimalista. Es un solo espacio para ser vivido con intimidad. Es el lugar perfecto para disfrutar en cualquier momento del día.
Más información y fotos @lovelyhousesdiana

The space
Más información y fotos @lovelyhousesdiana
Dispone de una cocina americana totalmente equipada, el dormitorio está separado del resto de la vivienda por una cortina de madera blanca que da intimidad, con cama doble de látex más un topper de 160cm, un baño con ducha y un gran patio privado con amplias vistas a los campos.
Es el lugar perfecto para disfrutar en cualquier momento del día.
COMODIDADES
Capacidad para 2 personas y un bebé

Wifi gratuito, Sábanas y toallas, Secador de pelo y tabla de planchar, Lavadora, Bola para lavar ecológica, Tendedero, Frigorífico y congelador, Vitrocerámica, Horno, Microondas, Aspiradora, Ollas, Sart
neighborhood_overview:
El loft está emplazado en un camino a 2 kilómetros de Sant Jordi Desvalls. Es un lugar donde reina la tranquilidad y el silencio. Un precioso paisaje de interior, rodeado de campos, huertos y bosques donde disfrutar de agradables paseos.
A escasos kilómetros de la casa se encuentran las playas más bonitas de la Costa Brava. A tan sólo 20 minutos en coche de l'Estartit, i l'Escala, y a 25 minutos de Girona. También podrás visitar numerosos pueblos con encanto. En la casa encontraríes la Guia de l'Empordà y recomandaciones.
En el pueblo de Sant Jordi Desvalls hay un pequeño supermercado de pueblo abierto todos los días; incluso los domingos.
host_about:
Nuestra familia siempre trabajó en el campo y nuestra ilusión de dar nueva vida a antiguos espacios utilizados para el ganado y sus cultivos nos llevaron a construir estas magníficas casas, respetando siempre el entorno y los lugares, con materiales honestos y de calidad.. 
Estaremos encantados de daros la bienvenida y explicaros lo que creemos es lo mejor y más bonito de la zona del Empordà y el Gironès.

name: 13 Calle Santa Maria In the heart of old Cadaqués
description:
In the heart of old Cadaqués, between the sea, 100 meters away, and Santa Maria Church, with its baroque altarpiece 23 m high, this family house can accommodate up to 10 people. Built on two floors, it has a large patio where between sun and shade you can have lunch and take a nap. On the second floor, a bay window overlooking the Riba Pitxot with its famous arcade painted by Dali, Picasso and many other painters who made Cadaqués their place of inspiration.

The space
This is an old house bought by my family in the 1950s when fresh water arrived by tanker. The current kitchen is installed in the old cistern. We tried to maintain the house in its original appearance by equipping it with a kitchen and modern bathrooms.

Guest access
The house is entirely up to you.

Other things to note
It is not possible to reach the house directly by car.
We advise you to park at Port-Alguer while you carry your luggage inside.
neighborhood_overview: The house is located in the old Cadaqués next to the Santa Maria church to visit for its altarpiece, near the town hall where often floats the Catalan flag and offers a beautiful view of the whole bay. This area is full of craft shops and small restaurants. The beach of Port-Alguer is a hundred meters where Ribat Pixot is famous for its arch and its view of the church and its tapas bar.

name: Rustic "Mas" farmhouse Emporda/Costa Brava/Girona
description:
Our wonderful rustic "Mas" farmhouse full of character in the quiet and serene Gavarres Nature Park/Baix Emporda between Palamos and Mont Ras near Palafrugell and Calella... far from the maddening crowd but just a stone's throw away from the beaches of Castell, La Fosca, Cala Estreta, etc on the Costa Brava.
Fully furnished & equipped by default, for 13 GUESTS.
However there is room, if necessary, for 2 more guests for an extra guest fee.

License # HUTG-017243

The space
Mas Cabré is a typical Catalan "mas" (farmhouse) built in 1842, according to the date chiseled on the front stone archway. However, it's been documented that a building of some kind already stood there in the 15th century. That's not surprising, since human presence in the area dates from prehistoric times and several dolmens and other Megalithic carvings can be found on the property or close to it.

During our renovations of Mas Cabré, we've kept its rustic, simp
neighborhood_overview:
Mas Cabre is all about location, location, location! You feel like you are far away from everything, almost in the middle of nowhere.

It is situated in the Gavarres Nature Park which is included in the European Union's Natura 2000 Network of protected areas whose goal is to ensure the long term survival of Europe's species and habitats in a sustainable manner.
The nearest house is 1 km away.
However you can see the sea from the house and the town and beaches of the Costa Brava are only minutes away.

Located in the beautifully scenic Baix Empordà region, in Catalonia, Mas Cabré belongs to the municipalities of Vall-Llobrega and Forallac, an area rich with history, great food and sports activities.
From there, you can visit old medieval towns or go to the beach; you can indulge in lunch or dinner by the sea or surrounded by nature; or you can visit a local winery and experience a wine tour.
And let's not forget bicycle trips, sailing, fishing
host_about:
I am a native New Yorker but have lived more years in Barcelona than in New York.
Profession: Freelance photographer specialized in commercial architecture, interiors and portrait photography as well as documentary photography projects on forest related climate change issues.

name: Maison de pêcheur vue mer, grand jardin
description:
Maison de cachet située dans un grand jardin au milieu des oliviers. Un petit coin de paradis pour se relaxer et se reposer, idéal pour les parents et les enfants, à 5 min à pieds de la plage. Belle vue sur la mer et la montagne. Possibilité de garer plusieurs voitures.

The space
La maison est traditionnelle mais totalement rénovée avec tout le confort moderne. Grand espace extérieur et barbecue. La 3ème chambre est bien pour les enfants (petits ou ados) car elle est sous les toits, en pente, et moins pratique pour les adultes car plafond relativement bas (pas idéale pour les tout petits car petit escalier raide).

Guest access
Tout confort: machine à laver le linge, la vaisselle, douche extérieure avec eau chaude, grand coin barbecue, jeux pour les enfants - ping-pong, badminton, jeux de société. 5 min à pieds des plages et bars de plage de Cadaques (3 guinguettes restaurants - bars).

Other things to note

name: La Palmera 1, Apartment
description:
Apartment located on the ground floor, on the coastal side of the building "La Palmera". Consisting of two double bedrooms, bathroom with shower, kitchen, lounge-dining room and terrace with sea views. The very bright rooms for their windows directly overlooking a street of the village, have a double bed and two single beds. The galley kitchen gives access to the living-dining room, which is the largest room of the apartment. All this space open to the outside and to the terrace by a large glass door, is therefore an important source of natural light. The terrace, which is an extension of the living room, has sea views and a set of table and chairs for enjoying alfresco dining.

name: Loft en la Fageda d'en Jordà
description:
Loft moderno construido en la primera planta de la casa, zona garaje, funcional, muy luminoso y con salida a un pequeño jardín. Cuenta con 2 camas de matrimonio de 135 cm, sofá, estufa de leña, nevera, microondas, tostadora, cafetera Nespresso, vitrocerámica de dos fuegos, extractor de humos, utensilios básicos de cocina, TV LCD 32". Tiene un lavabo con ducha y wc exclusivo para los huéspedes y una zona para juegos y mesa de ping pong. Al lado del jardín hay un gallinero con 5 gallinas.

The space
Loft ideal para familias de 4 personas. Está a 100 metros de la reserva natural de la Fageda d'en Jordà, que comprende un bosque de hayas de características únicas en España.

Guest access
Jardín y garaje.

Other things to note
En las fechas del 17 de julio hasta el 29 de agosto 2021 estancia mínima 6 noches, con entradas en sabados y domingos.

name: La Sirenita Apartment - HUTG-018865-86
description:
A fantastic location front line to the sea - superb location, free ADSL WiFi!
TV in Spanish, French, German and some English available.
Parking space in front of apt! Walking distance of 7 minutes to beach Palangres, walk to Canyelles Petites (10 mins) or town of Roses with large choice of restaurants, bars!
Hear the sea from the apartment and just walk down the steps onto the coastal path and direct access to the rocks to swim and sunbathe. The apartment is on the ground level so easy access!

The space
Front line to the sea with superb sea views and over the Bay of Roses to the Isle of Medes in the distance which can be enjoyed from the outside private terrace for dining or the open planned kitchen/dining room/ lounge. The bedroom is spacious with one double bed and fitted wardrobes and there is a sofa bed in the lounge. It is perfect for 2 adults. No car needed!
TV offers: Full Spanish, Full French, Full German and some English and other eu
neighborhood_overview:
This area of the coast of Costa Brava is just beautiful! I have traveled all over the world and this area is hard to beat!
There are many things to see and do in this area including most types of water sports, boat trips, water park, go karts, horse riding, cycling, sky diving (wind tunnel also available) in Empuriabrava plus much more.
Out of season it is very quiet and a superb location for walking.
If you like walking then it's perfect to enjoy the stunning scenery along the coastal path or up into the national park of Cap de Creus or take a boat trip along the coast round to Cadaques which is really worth while.

You can walk to the sandy cove of Palangrers (7 mins), Canyelles Petites (10-15 mins), Almadrava (20-30 mins) or Roses main beach and town in under 15 minutes. If you want to hike further you can walk to many other coves along the coastal path including Cala Montjoi, Cala Joncols, walk to Cadaques or even further afield time permitting!
It i
host_about:
Hi, I love to travel although do not do enough of it nowadays! I like to think that our guests have the best experience in our accommodations, that they have everything they need and a very comfortable stay.
This area is fantastic to explore and we do all we can to make sure you enjoy it as much as we do. We have lived her for 18 years+!
I hope we meet soon!

name: Sleep & Stay Duplex apt in Old Town
description:
Cozy city apartment, divided over two levels with one bedroom. Beautifully decorated, to make you feel at home in Girona straight away! Located close to the Sant Feliu church in Calle Barca.

The space
Cozy city apartment, divided over two levels with one bedroom. Beautifully decorated, to make you feel at home in Girona straight away! Located close to the Sant Feliu church in Calle Barca.

This beautifully apartment is located on the third floor. The apartment has high ceilings and has a bright and spacious living space on the first level. There is an open kitchen, with an open bar to the big dining table suitable for 6 guests. There is a sleeping sofa for an extra 2 guests and a cot available on demand. On the second level there is a bathroom with a bath, a little office area and main bedroom. This bedroom is not on the main street side, so a nice and quit room for a good nights rest after a long day in Girona’s old town!

Guest access
neighborhood_overview: sin registro
host_about:
Sleep and Stay is a professional holiday rental agency and licensed Real estate Agency.
All our properties are carefully selected and we prioritize customer service, a personal touch and impecable cleaning. We leave a welcome package with cleaning products (dishwasher tablets, laundry tablets, sponge, cloth and extra garbage bags) and first essentials like coffee, tea, sugar, salt, pepper, olive oil and vinegar. Those items you just need for a couple of days away, are just great to have at your disposal. 
Most people that visit Girona once, never want to leave again. They want to come back, because Girona has it all. We recently opened a branch in Besalu which is small medieval copy of Girona. We have beaches, culture of Dali, the great Spanish kitchen with lot’s of different tapas and wines, old medieval villages and mountains great for skiing, hiking and cycling! What else do you want?

That’s why we fell in love with Girona and made it our business of helping people to find their dream holiday home for a week’s stay or even to buy a property and have a second home in this amazing region! Sleep & Stay is owned by Jolien Huizing Gerrans, Dutch nationality, and she has surrounded herself by an amazing team. Sonia (Polish) and Luis (Honduras). We personally manage each holiday property that are featured on this website and are experts in the Girona property market for more than 4 years. We all speak next to our mother tongues Spanish, Catalan and English which makes all language barriers disappear!

As a young and dynamic holiday rental organisation, specialised in amazing holiday rentals, property management and property finder services. We can assist you in finding a special place to stay in Girona. We value quality, comfort and well maintained holiday rentals as our most important goals. We want to find that charming place for you that makes you fall in love with Girona too and makes you want to stay forever.

Once you arrive and you need anything, we are here to help you. Available on (Hidden by Airbnb) , email and we're just a phone call away. Welcome to come and stay with us!

description:

The space
Casa Dos Torres is a registered "pension" in Calella de Palafrugell.
We described ourselves as a Bed and Breakfast but this category does not exist here in Sapin therefore we have been given the registration "P" by the Generalitat de Catalunya.

Guest access

Other things to note
neighborhood_overview:
Calella de Palafrugell is an old fishing village. It's centre has retained the original "look" of the place but it has grown considerably over the years.
It still does retain a charm and beauty which attracts people from all over the world.
Calella de Palafrugell is a well known seaside "village in The Costa Brava much frequented by the local Catalans.
The first Saturday in July each year there is the Havanares Festival.
Throughout July and August the Cap Roig gardens hold regular concerts.
This year there may not be concerts!

The space

En el baño dispon
neighborhood_overview:
Lo que mas me gusta de donde vivo es que estoy lo bastante lejos del ajetreo y tráfico de la ciudad, pero muy cerca de todo. Todos los servicios (supermercados, farmacias, tiendas, restaurantes, bares,etc...) los tienes a 5 minutos en coche.
Es una zona residencial muy tranquila. Con una plaza delante de casa y sin problemas para aparcar.
Hay un Hostal que tiene servicio de bar y restaurante a 1 minuto a pie de casa.
Para hacer las compras puedes ir a Cornella del Terri que hay un pequeño supermercado, carnicería, verdulería, panadería, farmácia y dos bancos "La CAIXA" y Banco Popular se encuentra a unos 800m de casa (mejor en coche). La otra opción es ir a comprar en Banyoles, esta a 3km, 5minutos en coche. Donde encontraras todos los supermercados en el mismo lugar ( Mercadona, Aldi, Dia, Lidl, Bon Preu,etc ....)
En 10 minutos estas en el lago de Banyoles donde podrás relajarte, pasear y respirar tranquilamente.
A 15 minutos estas en el centro de Girona,
host_about:
Tengo 44 años, dos hijas estupendas y  dos gatos .
Soy positiva y alegre. Me gusta hacer deporte y todo lo relacionado con la salud.
Intercambiar experiencias con otras personas me encanta.
Cada día es una oportunidad y cada oportunidad una experiencia.

neighborhood_overview:
Platja d'Aro is an animated town in the heart of the Costa Brava, which is known for its beaches but also for its gastronomy and its wine. The city hosts many festivals during the summer such as the free "Nits the Jazz", which hosts jazz concerts once a week during the whole summer.

There is a lot of restaurants, bars, nightclubs as well as outdoors activities, such as minigolfs,acquatic activities, horse riding and many walking or cycling routes in the area.

Moreover, the well-know Golf d'Aro is minutes away from the house, on the same hill.

A small food store is a five-minute drive away, on the hill, in the Hapimag complex.

The house is approximately 1 hour away from Barcelona, 30min from Girona. There is also numerous traditional villages in the area.

description:
Acogedora masía ampurdanesa, muy bien restaurada y equipada. Está situada a muy poca distancia de Banyoles, Girona y de las playas de la Costa Brava, por lo que permite hacer visitas culturales, rutas gastronómicas y numerosas actividades al aire libre.

Masía del siglo XVIII rodeada de jardín con piscina, bosques y campos de cultivo. La casa cuenta con cuatro habitaciones, todas con baño privado, y las estancias, que conservan los bonitos techos abovedados, están decoradas con un estilo rústico y elegante. La cocina abierta con el comedor y también la sala de estar cuentan con chimenea.

Cottage form the seventeenth century restored in 2015. The house is in a quiet area surrounded by nature.
It has 4 bedrooms with private bathrooms, kitchen, living room and large garden with pool.

neighborhood_overview:
The Old Town of Girona is considered the historical center of the city, bounded by the medieval city wall, part of which was demolished in the nineteenth century, and is where we find the most important historic and cultural attractions of the city.
The houses on the river Onyar are a sight which must be enjoyed from one of the bridges crossing the river, and we approach the Jewish quarter from the Rambla. In the promenade bustle of visitors and locals, strolling, shopping, resting live.
Once entered in the Jewish Quarter, one of the best preserved in Spain, we can enjoy the historic legacy of the city, letting lose through the narrow streets and right steps, discovering corners, gardens, monuments and churches, between steps. The Cathedral, the church of Sant Feliu, the Arab Baths, Sant Pere de Galligants.

Soy una amante del arte y de la decoración.

Espero os guste el apartamento que ofrezco que he decorado con tanto cariño.

Os espero pronto!

description:
This amazing villa was completely refurbished to a very high standard for the 2017 season. It has six air conditioned bedrooms, three doubles, two twins and a triple and 5 beautiful bathrooms. The villa has its own swimming pool which is adjacent to a large terrace with great views of the sea and the Islas Medes.

fast interne
neighborhood_overview:
The villa is situated in one of the most beautiful areas of Spain – the Costa Brava. The Costa Brava is a rocky coastline, plentiful in coves, secluded beaches and little fishing villages. The beautiful beach of Sa Riera, right in the heart of this coast and recognised as being one of the jewels of the Costa Brava, is about 15 minutes walk from the villa.

Begur, a well-known medieval town is about 10 minutes walk. from Villa Begur. Begur has cobbled streets, with a large central square surrounded by pavement cafes. There is a great mixture of fine restaurants, tapas bars, and even a fantastic open air pizza restaurant. There are also plenty of late night bars which cater mostly to the style conscious Barcelonians, no English pubs or rave clubs in this town. There are also many stylish independant boutiques which, in the Summer months, are open late into the cool evenings.

This part of the Costa Brava is much more a getaway for Spaniards than it is a mecca for fore
host_about: The Blandfords have owned Villa Begur since 2003 and Villa Sa Riera since 2016. We love the area and spend much of the Summer there if we can.

neighborhood_overview:
Sa Riera is one of the largest beaches in Begur, and the closest to the town.
It is excellently located, with the sheltered Port d’Es Pi cove to the right, and the Rei cove to the left . Sa Riera takes its name from a stream dividing the beach in half, it has kept its traditional character with low rise buildings and the pine covered surrounding hills. It offers a range of different sports activities and tourist services.
There are various bars and restaurants to enjoy the gastronomy of the region, and also a few shops, including a supermarket.
From Sa Riera one can walk the costal trail to the beaches of Platja del Racó and Pals.
host_about:
Originally from Barcelona, but I lived many years in the UK and for a few years now I’ve settled down with my husband Richard and our three grown up sons in Besalú, just north of Girona.
I love walking in the nature, practicing yoga and pilates, healthy food and crafts. I adore little villages with cobbled pavements and narrow streets, and balconies full of flowers.  But I also need regular doses of city life!  Shops, bars, cafes, busy streets, and lively markets.
My favourite season is spring, I like it hot and sunny! I love the smell of freshly cut grass and my favourite colour is the tourquoise green-blue of the Costa Brava waters!
I consider myself a social and friendly person, love meeting new people and discovering new places.
I will be delighted to welcome you!

neighborhood_overview:
Canyelles is a lovely beach area with a few bars and restaurants near the beach.

The area has houses built into the hills with no high rise hotels in sight.

It's just a 5 minute walk to Canyelles beach, bars, restaurants and mini-market. Directly opposite the apartment are steps taking you down to the costal path which you can take to Canyelles beach or if you keep on walking you'll come to Almadraba beach after about 20 minutes, which has lovely beach bars and restaurants. Keep on walking and you will come to the National Park which is a great walk if you are fit.

Head in the opposite direction and Roses is only a 25/30 minute walk. There is also a regular bus service to Roses during the summer.

Roses is only a 5 minute drive away.

Good for cyclists and for walkers there's a great costal path leading into the port in Roses.

neighborhood_overview:
The Old Town of Girona is considered the historical center of the city, bounded by the medieval city wall, part of which was demolished in the nineteenth century, and is where we find the most important historic and cultural attractions of the city.
The houses on the river Onyar are a sight which must be enjoyed from one of the bridges crossing the river, and we approach the Jewish quarter from the Rambla. In the promenade bustle of visitors and locals, strolling, shopping, resting live.
Once entered in the Jewish Quarter, one of the best preserved in Spain, we can enjoy the historic legacy of the city, letting lose through the narrow streets and right steps, discovering corners, gardens, monuments and churches, between steps. The Cathedral, the church of Sant Feliu, the Arab Baths, Sant Pere de Galligants.

neighborhood_overview:
Campelles is part of the Ripollès region, in the province of Girona.
It is a very well-preserved natural area with all kinds of fauna, ideal for short excursions along the river, with the option of bathing in its refreshing waters in summer. During the fall, it is a very good place to go looking for mushrooms, or in winter to ski on the nearby slopes of Vall de Núria, La Molina, Masella or Vallter 2000.The town also offers a great variety of local gastronomic products, they highlight its sausages and cheeses, honey or biscuits from Camprodon, near Campelles, are also highly appreciated.

neighborhood_overview:
The Costa Brava has a wealth of wonderful places and cuisine for the visitor to experience. The area has some of the most beautiful beaches and hidden coves in Europe, for guests to explore. There is an unlimited amount of water sports from kayaking, boat hire, windsurfing/boarding and other water-borne sports to enjoy. The Medes islands, just off the coast of Estartit, is a protected marine area and has some of the best diving experiences in the Mediterranean. There are great cycling routes and for the more tranquil pursuits, there are wonderful walks and bird watching opportunities.

Examples of occupying civilisations from the ancient Iberians to the Greeks and Romans, have all left their mark on the landscape of this area. The area also has a wealth of wonderful historical buildings/architecture for guests who wish to explore the history and culture of the area. The medieval towns/villages of Castello d'Empuries, Pals, Peratallada, San Marti and Torroella de Montgri

host_about:
Since young I have been a lover of travel, to meet new people and cultures. Relying on the kindness of stranger I had precious and unforgettable experiences.
Since we moved to the Costa Brava of Girona with my husband, we have rented or exchanged our house on several occasions with foreign and Spanish families. It has always been a positive experience. Now we live in the city of Girona.

LA ZONA . LA GARROTXA
La Garrotxa disfruta de dos tipos de paisaje totalmente distintos, peculiares y de una gran belleza.
Por una parte la Zona Volcánica, 40 volcanes y coladas de lava que crean un paisaje absolutamente único y por otra parte el Espacio de Interés Nacional de la Alta Garrotxa, que abarca el Valle del Rio Fluvià hacia el Norte, donde el paisaje cambia radicalmente volviéndose abrupto y escarpado, y donde podemos observar espacios naturales de una especial belleza.

Masia de tres plantas, se alquilan las tres habitaciones de la planta superior con un baño a compartir.
Los anfitriones viven el la casa.
Amplia sala con chimenea.

The space
La casa está situada en medio de la naturaleza pero a 300m del pueblo.
Es una típica masia catalana de tres plantas que se ha restaurado conservando la esencia de la época y el entorno.
La planta baja dispone de una amplia cocina, un acogedor comedor y una gran sala con chimenea para pasar agradables veladas al calor del hogar.
En la planta alta están situadas tres habitaciones dobles y un baño completo, destinado a acoger a nuestros huéspedes.
En la planta intermedia es donde se aloja Roser y su familia, la anfitriona.

Guest access

neighborhood_overview:

La zona ofrece la posibilidad de realizar preciosas excursiones andando, en bicicleta, a caballo, en globo...
El municipio se encuentra situado a la cabecera de río Fluvià, cercado por las sierras del Corb, de Sant Miquel de Llancers y por el Puigsacalm (1515 m).
Fantástica gastronomía y embutidos.
Se encuentra cerca de preciosos pueblos medievales como Santa Pau, Besalú... De La Fageda d'en Jordà, de volcanes, vías de escalada...

The space
La casa totalmente nueva esta esperando que viajeros con ganas de tranquilidad vengan a disfrutar de la calma de su jardín, el lugar en el que seguro disfrutarán tumbados en la zona Chile out acompañados de unacopa de vino del Emporda que gustosamente pondremos a su disposición.

host_about:
Me gusta disfrutar de mi tiempo libre rodeado de las personas que me hacen sentir bien, por eso suelo compartir muchos momentos agradables con mis amigos. Mi casa del Estartit suele ser uno de los lugares de reunión, en ella siempre hay alguna botella de vino preparada para descorchar y acompañarla de un buen queso.
Mis grandes pasiones son viajar, el futbol y una buena comida maridada con un buen vino.

host_about:
Hola,
Mi nombre es Marc. Tengo 44 años.
Estoy licenciado en historia y durante años he trabajado en el ámbito del deporte y el ocio infantil.
Actualmente también gestiono en airbnb el proyecto "Seafront L'Estartit Apartments" con mi familia. Me considero un anfitrión atento, respetuoso y amable. Y creo que airbnb es una fantástica plataforma para establecer una relación basada en estos principios.
Abrimos las puertas de dos apartamentos familiares, céntricos y a primera línea de mar. Con unas privilegiadas vistas del Mediterraneo y las islas Medas.
En nuestro espacio recibiréis un trato hospitalario y caluroso, y a su vez una gestión moderna del alojamiento y sus servicios.
Rehuimos del modelo turístico a gran escala en favor de una relación respetuosa y afectuosa.
Bienvenidos!

name: Apartment Golf Mar
description:
The Golf Mar apartments are located close to the port of L´Escala on the beautiful Costa Brava.
The Golf Mar apartment complex has a communal pool located in well kept gardens with plenty of sun. The apartment is on the first floor and consists of one bedroom with double bed and one bedroom with two single beds.
The double bedroom has access to the rear balcony overlooking the pool and gardens.
This apartment boasts a large lounge, dining area and kitchen area which has access to a balcony overlooking pine woods and with a sea view of the bay of Roses.
The beach of Riells is located at about 15 mins walk.
The beach front has numerous bars and restaurants. Local supermarket are also located here. In peak season a funfair is located at the far end of Riells beach which is approx 20 mins walk. The old village of L`Escala approx a further 15 mins walk.

description:
Casa de vacaciones en SantMori bonito pueblo medieval del Alt Empordà, a medio camino de Figueres (con su magnifico museo Dali) y Girona( con su fascinante Barri Vell), y la proximidad de las playas de la Costa Brava la convierten en un lugar ideal.

neighborhood_overview:
Sant Mori es un pueblo rural de unos doscientos habitantes que se halla en la comarca del Ampurdán, situado a medio camino entre Figueras (25 km), hogar de la Casa Museo Dalí, y Gerona (38 km), una pequeña ciudad amurallada con interesantes museos y restaurantes, donde encontramos el Call o barrio judío, uno de los más extensos y mejor conservados de Europa.

Las playas de la Costa Brava y las ruinas de Ampurias se encuentran a menos de 10 km.

Situado a 130 km de Barcelona. Por el norte, la frontera con Francia a solo 60 km. y Perpignan, la ciudad francesa más cercana, se encuentra a 84 km.

Apartment in House Estor, neoclassic mansion(small palace) of s. The XIXth placed in the heart of the Jewish neighborhood, to three minutes afoot(by foot) of the points of interest

The space
Situated in the oldest part of Girona it is moments away from the Cathedral, the city walls and all the points of interest in the town. neighborhood_overview:
The location in the centre of old Girona is ideal for tourists. All the significant historic and cultural sites are within a few moments walk. It allows visitors to live like locals in the most historic and prestigious part of the city.

There are also many enjoyable day trips from Girona. It is a short drive to the beaches, coastal villages and stunning views of the Costa Brava. Visitors can also travel inland to the medieval villages of Besalú, Monells or Bisbal and its ceramics. There are the extinct volcanos of Olot to visit as well. Figueras, the birth place of Salvador Dalí and home of the Dalí museum is close by. The train station is a 15 minute walk away and Barcelona is 30 minutes by high speed train.
